32#ifdef _MSC_VER
33char *basename(const char* path)
34{
35 char* base1 = (char*)strrchr(path, '/');
36 char* base2 = (char*)strrchr(path, '\\');
37 if (base1 && base2)
38 return((base1 > base2) ? base1 + 1 : base2 + 1);
39 else if (base1)
40 return(base1 + 1);
41 else if (base2)
42 return(base2 + 1);
43
44 return((char*)path);
45}
46char *dirname(char* path)
47{
48 char* base1 = (char*)strrchr(path, '/');
49 char* base2 = (char*)strrchr(path, '\\');
50 if (base1 && base2)
51 if (base1 > base2)
52 *base1 = 0;
53 else
54 *base2 = 0;
55 else if (base1)
56 *base1 = 0;
57 else if (base2)
58 *base2 = 0;
59
60 return path;
61}
62#else
63extern char *basename(const char *);
64extern char *dirname(char *);
65#endif

67/** Return the default parsing options. */
68static unsigned getDefaultParsingOptions() {
69 unsigned options = CXTranslationUnit_DetailedPreprocessingRecord;
70
71 if (getenv("CINDEXTEST_EDITING"))
72 options |= clang_defaultEditingTranslationUnitOptions();
73 if (getenv("CINDEXTEST_COMPLETION_CACHING"))
74 options |= CXTranslationUnit_CacheCompletionResults;
75 if (getenv("CINDEXTEST_COMPLETION_NO_CACHING"))
76 options &= ~CXTranslationUnit_CacheCompletionResults;
77 if (getenv("CINDEXTEST_SKIP_FUNCTION_BODIES"))
78 options |= CXTranslationUnit_SkipFunctionBodies;
79 if (getenv("CINDEXTEST_COMPLETION_BRIEF_COMMENTS"))
80 options |= CXTranslationUnit_IncludeBriefCommentsInCodeCompletion;
81 if (getenv("CINDEXTEST_CREATE_PREAMBLE_ON_FIRST_PARSE"))
82 options |= CXTranslationUnit_CreatePreambleOnFirstParse;
83 if (getenv("CINDEXTEST_KEEP_GOING"))
84 options |= CXTranslationUnit_KeepGoing;
85 if (getenv("CINDEXTEST_LIMIT_SKIP_FUNCTION_BODIES_TO_PREAMBLE"))
86 options |= CXTranslationUnit_LimitSkipFunctionBodiesToPreamble;
87 if (getenv("CINDEXTEST_INCLUDE_ATTRIBUTED_TYPES"))
88 options |= CXTranslationUnit_IncludeAttributedTypes;
89 if (getenv("CINDEXTEST_VISIT_IMPLICIT_ATTRIBUTES"))
90 options |= CXTranslationUnit_VisitImplicitAttributes;
91 if (getenv("CINDEXTEST_IGNORE_NONERRORS_FROM_INCLUDED_FILES"))
92 options |= CXTranslationUnit_IgnoreNonErrorsFromIncludedFiles;
93
94 return options;
95}

98 struct Mapping {
99 const char *name;
100 enum CXPrintingPolicyProperty property;
101 };
102 struct Mapping mappings[] = {
103 {"CINDEXTEST_PRINTINGPOLICY_INDENTATION", CXPrintingPolicy_Indentation},
104 {"CINDEXTEST_PRINTINGPOLICY_SUPPRESSSPECIFIERS",
105 CXPrintingPolicy_SuppressSpecifiers},
106 {"CINDEXTEST_PRINTINGPOLICY_SUPPRESSTAGKEYWORD",
107 CXPrintingPolicy_SuppressTagKeyword},
108 {"CINDEXTEST_PRINTINGPOLICY_INCLUDETAGDEFINITION",
109 CXPrintingPolicy_IncludeTagDefinition},
110 {"CINDEXTEST_PRINTINGPOLICY_SUPPRESSSCOPE",
111 CXPrintingPolicy_SuppressScope},
112 {"CINDEXTEST_PRINTINGPOLICY_SUPPRESSUNWRITTENSCOPE",
113 CXPrintingPolicy_SuppressUnwrittenScope},
114 {"CINDEXTEST_PRINTINGPOLICY_SUPPRESSINITIALIZERS",
115 CXPrintingPolicy_SuppressInitializers},
116 {"CINDEXTEST_PRINTINGPOLICY_CONSTANTARRAYSIZEASWRITTEN",
117 CXPrintingPolicy_ConstantArraySizeAsWritten},
118 {"CINDEXTEST_PRINTINGPOLICY_ANONYMOUSTAGLOCATIONS",
119 CXPrintingPolicy_AnonymousTagLocations},
120 {"CINDEXTEST_PRINTINGPOLICY_SUPPRESSSTRONGLIFETIME",
121 CXPrintingPolicy_SuppressStrongLifetime},
122 {"CINDEXTEST_PRINTINGPOLICY_SUPPRESSLIFETIMEQUALIFIERS",
123 CXPrintingPolicy_SuppressLifetimeQualifiers},
124 {"CINDEXTEST_PRINTINGPOLICY_SUPPRESSTEMPLATEARGSINCXXCONSTRUCTORS",
125 CXPrintingPolicy_SuppressTemplateArgsInCXXConstructors},
126 {"CINDEXTEST_PRINTINGPOLICY_BOOL", CXPrintingPolicy_Bool},
127 {"CINDEXTEST_PRINTINGPOLICY_RESTRICT", CXPrintingPolicy_Restrict},
128 {"CINDEXTEST_PRINTINGPOLICY_ALIGNOF", CXPrintingPolicy_Alignof},
129 {"CINDEXTEST_PRINTINGPOLICY_UNDERSCOREALIGNOF",
130 CXPrintingPolicy_UnderscoreAlignof},
131 {"CINDEXTEST_PRINTINGPOLICY_USEVOIDFORZEROPARAMS",
132 CXPrintingPolicy_UseVoidForZeroParams},
133 {"CINDEXTEST_PRINTINGPOLICY_TERSEOUTPUT", CXPrintingPolicy_TerseOutput},
134 {"CINDEXTEST_PRINTINGPOLICY_POLISHFORDECLARATION",
135 CXPrintingPolicy_PolishForDeclaration},
136 {"CINDEXTEST_PRINTINGPOLICY_HALF", CXPrintingPolicy_Half},
137 {"CINDEXTEST_PRINTINGPOLICY_MSWCHAR", CXPrintingPolicy_MSWChar},
138 {"CINDEXTEST_PRINTINGPOLICY_INCLUDENEWLINES",
139 CXPrintingPolicy_IncludeNewlines},
140 {"CINDEXTEST_PRINTINGPOLICY_MSVCFORMATTING",

142 {"CINDEXTEST_PRINTINGPOLICY_CONSTANTSASWRITTEN",
143 CXPrintingPolicy_ConstantsAsWritten},
144 {"CINDEXTEST_PRINTINGPOLICY_SUPPRESSIMPLICITBASE",
145 CXPrintingPolicy_SuppressImplicitBase},
146 {"CINDEXTEST_PRINTINGPOLICY_FULLYQUALIFIEDNAME",
147 CXPrintingPolicy_FullyQualifiedName},
148 };
149
150 unsigned i;
151 for (i = 0; i < sizeof(mappings) / sizeof(struct Mapping); i++) {
152 char *value = getenv(mappings[i].name);
153 if (value) {
154 clang_PrintingPolicy_setProperty(Policy, mappings[i].property,
155 (unsigned)strtoul(value, 0L, 10));
156 }
157 }
158}

163static void describeLibclangFailure(enum CXErrorCode Err) {
164 switch (Err) {
165 case CXError_Success:
166 fprintf(stderr, "Success\n");
167 return;
168
169 case CXError_Failure:
170 fprintf(stderr, "Failure (no details available)\n");
171 return;
172
173 case CXError_Crashed:
174 fprintf(stderr, "Failure: libclang crashed\n");
175 return;
176
177 case CXError_InvalidArguments:
178 fprintf(stderr, "Failure: invalid arguments passed to a libclang routine\n");
179 return;
180
181 case CXError_ASTReadError:
182 fprintf(stderr, "Failure: AST deserialization error occurred\n");
183 return;
184 }
185}

187static void PrintExtent(FILE *out, unsigned begin_line, unsigned begin_column,
188 unsigned end_line, unsigned end_column) {
189 fprintf(out, "[%d:%d - %d:%d]", begin_line, begin_column,
190 end_line, end_column);
191}

193static unsigned CreateTranslationUnit(CXIndex Idx, const char *file,
194 CXTranslationUnit *TU) {
195 enum CXErrorCode Err = clang_createTranslationUnit2(Idx, file, TU);
196 if (Err != CXError_Success) {
197 fprintf(stderr, "Unable to load translation unit from '%s'!\n", file);
198 describeLibclangFailure(Err);
199 *TU = 0;
200 return 0;
201 }
202 return 1;
203}

205void free_remapped_files(struct CXUnsavedFile *unsaved_files,
206 int num_unsaved_files) {
207 int i;
208 for (i = 0; i != num_unsaved_files; ++i) {
209 free((char *)unsaved_files[i].Filename);
210 free((char *)unsaved_files[i].Contents);
211 }
212 free(unsaved_files);
213}
214
215static int parse_remapped_files_with_opt(const char *opt_name,
216 int argc, const char **argv,
217 int start_arg,
218 struct CXUnsavedFile **unsaved_files,
219 int *num_unsaved_files) {
220 int i;
221 int arg;
222 int prefix_len = strlen(opt_name);
223 int arg_indices[20];
224 *unsaved_files = 0;
225 *num_unsaved_files = 0;
226
227 /* Count the number of remapped files. */
228 for (arg = start_arg; arg < argc; ++arg) {
229 if (strncmp(argv[arg], opt_name, prefix_len))
230 continue;
231
232 assert(*num_unsaved_files < (int)(sizeof(arg_indices)/sizeof(int)));
233 arg_indices[*num_unsaved_files] = arg;
234 ++*num_unsaved_files;
235 }
236
237 if (*num_unsaved_files == 0)
238 return 0;
239
240 *unsaved_files
241 = (struct CXUnsavedFile *)malloc(sizeof(struct CXUnsavedFile) *
242 *num_unsaved_files);
243 assert(*unsaved_files);
244 for (i = 0; i != *num_unsaved_files; ++i) {
245 struct CXUnsavedFile *unsaved = *unsaved_files + i;
246 const char *arg_string = argv[arg_indices[i]] + prefix_len;
247 int filename_len;
248 char *filename;
249 char *contents;
250 FILE *to_file;
251 const char *sep = strchr(arg_string, ',');
252 if (!sep) {
253 fprintf(stderr,
254 "error: %sfrom:to argument is missing comma\n", opt_name);
255 free_remapped_files(*unsaved_files, i);
256 *unsaved_files = 0;
257 *num_unsaved_files = 0;
258 return -1;
259 }
260
261 /* Open the file that we're remapping to. */
262 to_file = fopen(sep + 1, "rb");
263 if (!to_file) {
264 fprintf(stderr, "error: cannot open file %s that we are remapping to\n",
265 sep + 1);
266 free_remapped_files(*unsaved_files, i);
267 *unsaved_files = 0;
268 *num_unsaved_files = 0;
269 return -1;
270 }
271
272 /* Determine the length of the file we're remapping to. */
273 fseek(to_file, 0, SEEK_END);
274 unsaved->Length = ftell(to_file);
275 fseek(to_file, 0, SEEK_SET);
276
277 /* Read the contents of the file we're remapping to. */
278 contents = (char *)malloc(unsaved->Length + 1);
279 assert(contents);
280 if (fread(contents, 1, unsaved->Length, to_file) != unsaved->Length) {
281 fprintf(stderr, "error: unexpected %s reading 'to' file %s\n",
282 (feof(to_file) ? "EOF" : "error"), sep + 1);
283 fclose(to_file);
284 free_remapped_files(*unsaved_files, i);
285 free(contents);
286 *unsaved_files = 0;
287 *num_unsaved_files = 0;
288 return -1;
289 }
290 contents[unsaved->Length] = 0;
291 unsaved->Contents = contents;
292
293 /* Close the file. */
294 fclose(to_file);
295
296 /* Copy the file name that we're remapping from. */
297 filename_len = sep - arg_string;
298 filename = (char *)malloc(filename_len + 1);
299 assert(filename);
300 memcpy(filename, arg_string, filename_len);
301 filename[filename_len] = 0;
302 unsaved->Filename = filename;
303 }
304
305 return 0;
306}

308static int parse_remapped_files(int argc, const char **argv, int start_arg,
309 struct CXUnsavedFile **unsaved_files,
310 int *num_unsaved_files) {
311 return parse_remapped_files_with_opt("-remap-file=", argc, argv, start_arg,
312 unsaved_files, num_unsaved_files);
313}
314
315static int parse_remapped_files_with_try(int try_idx,
316 int argc, const char **argv,
317 int start_arg,
318 struct CXUnsavedFile **unsaved_files,
319 int *num_unsaved_files) {
320 struct CXUnsavedFile *unsaved_files_no_try_idx;
321 int num_unsaved_files_no_try_idx;
322 struct CXUnsavedFile *unsaved_files_try_idx;
323 int num_unsaved_files_try_idx;
324 int ret;
325 char opt_name[32];
326
327 ret = parse_remapped_files(argc, argv, start_arg,
328 &unsaved_files_no_try_idx, &num_unsaved_files_no_try_idx);
329 if (ret)
330 return ret;
331
332 sprintf(opt_name, "-remap-file-%d=", try_idx);
333 ret = parse_remapped_files_with_opt(opt_name, argc, argv, start_arg,
334 &unsaved_files_try_idx, &num_unsaved_files_try_idx);
335 if (ret)
336 return ret;
337
338 if (num_unsaved_files_no_try_idx == 0) {
339 *unsaved_files = unsaved_files_try_idx;
340 *num_unsaved_files = num_unsaved_files_try_idx;
341 return 0;
342 }
343 if (num_unsaved_files_try_idx == 0) {
344 *unsaved_files = unsaved_files_no_try_idx;
345 *num_unsaved_files = num_unsaved_files_no_try_idx;
346 return 0;
347 }
348
349 *num_unsaved_files = num_unsaved_files_no_try_idx + num_unsaved_files_try_idx;
350 *unsaved_files
351 = (struct CXUnsavedFile *)realloc(unsaved_files_no_try_idx,
352 sizeof(struct CXUnsavedFile) *
353 *num_unsaved_files);
354 assert(*unsaved_files);
355 memcpy(*unsaved_files + num_unsaved_files_no_try_idx,
356 unsaved_files_try_idx, sizeof(struct CXUnsavedFile) *
357 num_unsaved_files_try_idx);
358 free(unsaved_files_try_idx);
359 return 0;
360}

362static const char *parse_comments_schema(int argc, const char **argv) {
363 const char *CommentsSchemaArg = "-comments-xml-schema=";
364 const char *CommentSchemaFile = NULL;
365
366 if (argc == 0)
367 return CommentSchemaFile;
368
369 if (!strncmp(argv[0], CommentsSchemaArg, strlen(CommentsSchemaArg)))
370 CommentSchemaFile = argv[0] + strlen(CommentsSchemaArg);
371
372 return CommentSchemaFile;
373}

381static void PrintCString(const char *CStr) {
382 if (CStr != NULL && CStr[0] != '\0') {
383 for ( ; *CStr; ++CStr) {
384 const char C = *CStr;
385 switch (C) {
386 case '\n': printf("\\n"); break;
387 case '\r': printf("\\r"); break;
388 case '\t': printf("\\t"); break;
389 case '\v': printf("\\v"); break;
390 case '\f': printf("\\f"); break;
391 default: putchar(C); break;
392 }
393 }
394 }
395}
396
397static void PrintCStringWithPrefix(const char *Prefix, const char *CStr) {
398 printf(" %s=[", Prefix);
399 PrintCString(CStr);
400 printf("]");
401}
402
403static void PrintCXStringAndDispose(CXString Str) {
404 PrintCString(clang_getCString(Str));
405 clang_disposeString(Str);
406}
407
408static void PrintCXStringWithPrefix(const char *Prefix, CXString Str) {
409 PrintCStringWithPrefix(Prefix, clang_getCString(Str));
410}
411
412static void PrintCXStringWithPrefixAndDispose(const char *Prefix,
413 CXString Str) {
414 PrintCStringWithPrefix(Prefix, clang_getCString(Str));
415 clang_disposeString(Str);
416}

418static void PrintRange(CXSourceRange R, const char *str) {
419 CXFile begin_file, end_file;
420 unsigned begin_line, begin_column, end_line, end_column;
421
422 clang_getSpellingLocation(clang_getRangeStart(R),
423 &begin_file, &begin_line, &begin_column, 0);
424 clang_getSpellingLocation(clang_getRangeEnd(R),
425 &end_file, &end_line, &end_column, 0);
426 if (!begin_file || !end_file)
427 return;
428
429 if (str)
430 printf(" %s=", str);
431 PrintExtent(stdout, begin_line, begin_column, end_line, end_column);
432}

440static void printVersion(const char *Prefix, CXVersion Version) {
441 if (Version.Major < 0)
442 return;
443 printf("%s%d", Prefix, Version.Major);
444
445 if (Version.Minor < 0)
446 return;
447 printf(".%d", Version.Minor);
448
449 if (Version.Subminor < 0)
450 return;
451 printf(".%d", Version.Subminor);
452}

454struct CommentASTDumpingContext {
455 int IndentLevel;
456};
457
458static void DumpCXCommentInternal(struct CommentASTDumpingContext *Ctx,
459 CXComment Comment) {
460 unsigned i;
461 unsigned e;
462 enum CXCommentKind Kind = clang_Comment_getKind(Comment);
463
464 Ctx->IndentLevel++;
465 for (i = 0, e = Ctx->IndentLevel; i != e; ++i)
466 printf(" ");
467
468 printf("(");
469 switch (Kind) {
470 case CXComment_Null:
471 printf("CXComment_Null");
472 break;
473 case CXComment_Text:
474 printf("CXComment_Text");
475 PrintCXStringWithPrefixAndDispose("Text",
476 clang_TextComment_getText(Comment));
477 if (clang_Comment_isWhitespace(Comment))
478 printf(" IsWhitespace");
479 if (clang_InlineContentComment_hasTrailingNewline(Comment))
480 printf(" HasTrailingNewline");
481 break;
482 case CXComment_InlineCommand:
483 printf("CXComment_InlineCommand");
484 PrintCXStringWithPrefixAndDispose(
485 "CommandName",
486 clang_InlineCommandComment_getCommandName(Comment));
487 switch (clang_InlineCommandComment_getRenderKind(Comment)) {
488 case CXCommentInlineCommandRenderKind_Normal:
489 printf(" RenderNormal");
490 break;
491 case CXCommentInlineCommandRenderKind_Bold:
492 printf(" RenderBold");
493 break;
494 case CXCommentInlineCommandRenderKind_Monospaced:
495 printf(" RenderMonospaced");
496 break;
497 case CXCommentInlineCommandRenderKind_Emphasized:
498 printf(" RenderEmphasized");
499 break;
500 }
501 for (i = 0, e = clang_InlineCommandComment_getNumArgs(Comment);
502 i != e; ++i) {
503 printf(" Arg[%u]=", i);
504 PrintCXStringAndDispose(
505 clang_InlineCommandComment_getArgText(Comment, i));
506 }
507 if (clang_InlineContentComment_hasTrailingNewline(Comment))
508 printf(" HasTrailingNewline");
509 break;
510 case CXComment_HTMLStartTag: {
511 unsigned NumAttrs;
512 printf("CXComment_HTMLStartTag");
513 PrintCXStringWithPrefixAndDispose(
514 "Name",
515 clang_HTMLTagComment_getTagName(Comment));
516 NumAttrs = clang_HTMLStartTag_getNumAttrs(Comment);
517 if (NumAttrs != 0) {
518 printf(" Attrs:");
519 for (i = 0; i != NumAttrs; ++i) {
520 printf(" ");
521 PrintCXStringAndDispose(clang_HTMLStartTag_getAttrName(Comment, i));
522 printf("=");
523 PrintCXStringAndDispose(clang_HTMLStartTag_getAttrValue(Comment, i));
524 }
525 }
526 if (clang_HTMLStartTagComment_isSelfClosing(Comment))
527 printf(" SelfClosing");
528 if (clang_InlineContentComment_hasTrailingNewline(Comment))
529 printf(" HasTrailingNewline");
530 break;
531 }
532 case CXComment_HTMLEndTag:
533 printf("CXComment_HTMLEndTag");
534 PrintCXStringWithPrefixAndDispose(
535 "Name",
536 clang_HTMLTagComment_getTagName(Comment));
537 if (clang_InlineContentComment_hasTrailingNewline(Comment))
538 printf(" HasTrailingNewline");
539 break;
540 case CXComment_Paragraph:
541 printf("CXComment_Paragraph");
542 if (clang_Comment_isWhitespace(Comment))
543 printf(" IsWhitespace");
544 break;
545 case CXComment_BlockCommand:
546 printf("CXComment_BlockCommand");
547 PrintCXStringWithPrefixAndDispose(
548 "CommandName",
549 clang_BlockCommandComment_getCommandName(Comment));
550 for (i = 0, e = clang_BlockCommandComment_getNumArgs(Comment);
551 i != e; ++i) {
552 printf(" Arg[%u]=", i);
553 PrintCXStringAndDispose(
554 clang_BlockCommandComment_getArgText(Comment, i));
555 }
556 break;
557 case CXComment_ParamCommand:
558 printf("CXComment_ParamCommand");
559 switch (clang_ParamCommandComment_getDirection(Comment)) {
560 case CXCommentParamPassDirection_In:
561 printf(" in");
562 break;
563 case CXCommentParamPassDirection_Out:
564 printf(" out");
565 break;
566 case CXCommentParamPassDirection_InOut:
567 printf(" in,out");
568 break;
569 }
570 if (clang_ParamCommandComment_isDirectionExplicit(Comment))
571 printf(" explicitly");
572 else
573 printf(" implicitly");
574 PrintCXStringWithPrefixAndDispose(
575 "ParamName",
576 clang_ParamCommandComment_getParamName(Comment));
577 if (clang_ParamCommandComment_isParamIndexValid(Comment))
578 printf(" ParamIndex=%u", clang_ParamCommandComment_getParamIndex(Comment));
579 else
580 printf(" ParamIndex=Invalid");
581 break;
582 case CXComment_TParamCommand:
583 printf("CXComment_TParamCommand");
584 PrintCXStringWithPrefixAndDispose(
585 "ParamName",
586 clang_TParamCommandComment_getParamName(Comment));
587 if (clang_TParamCommandComment_isParamPositionValid(Comment)) {
588 printf(" ParamPosition={");
589 for (i = 0, e = clang_TParamCommandComment_getDepth(Comment);
590 i != e; ++i) {
591 printf("%u", clang_TParamCommandComment_getIndex(Comment, i));
592 if (i != e - 1)
593 printf(", ");
594 }
595 printf("}");
596 } else
597 printf(" ParamPosition=Invalid");
598 break;
599 case CXComment_VerbatimBlockCommand:
600 printf("CXComment_VerbatimBlockCommand");
601 PrintCXStringWithPrefixAndDispose(
602 "CommandName",
603 clang_BlockCommandComment_getCommandName(Comment));
604 break;
605 case CXComment_VerbatimBlockLine:
606 printf("CXComment_VerbatimBlockLine");
607 PrintCXStringWithPrefixAndDispose(
608 "Text",
609 clang_VerbatimBlockLineComment_getText(Comment));
610 break;
611 case CXComment_VerbatimLine:
612 printf("CXComment_VerbatimLine");
613 PrintCXStringWithPrefixAndDispose(
614 "Text",
615 clang_VerbatimLineComment_getText(Comment));
616 break;
617 case CXComment_FullComment:
618 printf("CXComment_FullComment");
619 break;
620 }
621 if (Kind != CXComment_Null) {
622 const unsigned NumChildren = clang_Comment_getNumChildren(Comment);
623 unsigned i;
624 for (i = 0; i != NumChildren; ++i) {
625 printf("\n// %s: ", FileCheckPrefix);
626 DumpCXCommentInternal(Ctx, clang_Comment_getChild(Comment, i));
627 }
628 }
629 printf(")");
630 Ctx->IndentLevel--;
631}
632
633static void DumpCXComment(CXComment Comment) {
634 struct CommentASTDumpingContext Ctx;
635 Ctx.IndentLevel = 1;
636 printf("\n// %s: CommentAST=[\n// %s:", FileCheckPrefix, FileCheckPrefix);
637 DumpCXCommentInternal(&Ctx, Comment);
638 printf("]");
639}

641static void ValidateCommentXML(const char *Str, const char *CommentSchemaFile) {
642#ifdef CLANG_HAVE_LIBXML
643 xmlRelaxNGParserCtxtPtr RNGParser;
644 xmlRelaxNGPtr Schema;
645 xmlDocPtr Doc;
646 xmlRelaxNGValidCtxtPtr ValidationCtxt;
647 int status;
648
649 if (!CommentSchemaFile)
650 return;
651
652 RNGParser = xmlRelaxNGNewParserCtxt(CommentSchemaFile);
653 if (!RNGParser) {
654 printf(" libXMLError");
655 return;
656 }
657 Schema = xmlRelaxNGParse(RNGParser);
658
659 Doc = xmlParseDoc((const xmlChar *) Str);
660
661 if (!Doc) {
662 xmlErrorPtr Error = xmlGetLastError();
663 printf(" CommentXMLInvalid [not well-formed XML: %s]", Error->message);
664 return;
665 }
666
667 ValidationCtxt = xmlRelaxNGNewValidCtxt(Schema);
668 status = xmlRelaxNGValidateDoc(ValidationCtxt, Doc);
669 if (!status)
670 printf(" CommentXMLValid");
671 else if (status > 0) {
672 xmlErrorPtr Error = xmlGetLastError();
673 printf(" CommentXMLInvalid [not valid XML: %s]", Error->message);
674 } else
675 printf(" libXMLError");
676
677 xmlRelaxNGFreeValidCtxt(ValidationCtxt);
678 xmlFreeDoc(Doc);
679 xmlRelaxNGFree(Schema);
680 xmlRelaxNGFreeParserCtxt(RNGParser);
681#endif
682}

684static void PrintCursorComments(CXCursor Cursor,
685 const char *CommentSchemaFile) {
686 {
687 CXString RawComment;
688 const char *RawCommentCString;
689 CXString BriefComment;
690 const char *BriefCommentCString;
691
692 RawComment = clang_Cursor_getRawCommentText(Cursor);
693 RawCommentCString = clang_getCString(RawComment);
694 if (RawCommentCString != NULL && RawCommentCString[0] != '\0') {
695 PrintCStringWithPrefix("RawComment", RawCommentCString);
696 PrintRange(clang_Cursor_getCommentRange(Cursor), "RawCommentRange");
697
698 BriefComment = clang_Cursor_getBriefCommentText(Cursor);
699 BriefCommentCString = clang_getCString(BriefComment);
700 if (BriefCommentCString != NULL && BriefCommentCString[0] != '\0')
701 PrintCStringWithPrefix("BriefComment", BriefCommentCString);
702 clang_disposeString(BriefComment);
703 }
704 clang_disposeString(RawComment);
705 }
706
707 {
708 CXComment Comment = clang_Cursor_getParsedComment(Cursor);
709 if (clang_Comment_getKind(Comment) != CXComment_Null) {
710 PrintCXStringWithPrefixAndDispose("FullCommentAsHTML",
711 clang_FullComment_getAsHTML(Comment));
712 {
713 CXString XML;
714 XML = clang_FullComment_getAsXML(Comment);
715 PrintCXStringWithPrefix("FullCommentAsXML", XML);
716 ValidateCommentXML(clang_getCString(XML), CommentSchemaFile);
717 clang_disposeString(XML);
718 }
719
720 DumpCXComment(Comment);
721 }
722 }
723}
724
725typedef struct {
726 unsigned line;
727 unsigned col;
728} LineCol;
729
730static int lineCol_cmp(const void *p1, const void *p2) {
731 const LineCol *lhs = p1;
732 const LineCol *rhs = p2;
733 if (lhs->line != rhs->line)
734 return (int)lhs->line - (int)rhs->line;
735 return (int)lhs->col - (int)rhs->col;
736}

738static CXString CursorToText(CXCursor Cursor) {
739 CXString text;
740 switch (wanted_display_type) {
741 case DisplayType_Spelling:
742 return clang_getCursorSpelling(Cursor);
743 case DisplayType_DisplayName:
744 return clang_getCursorDisplayName(Cursor);
745 case DisplayType_Pretty: {
746 CXPrintingPolicy Policy = clang_getCursorPrintingPolicy(Cursor);
747 ModifyPrintingPolicyAccordingToEnv(Policy);
748 text = clang_getCursorPrettyPrinted(Cursor, Policy);
749 clang_PrintingPolicy_dispose(Policy);
750 return text;
751 }
752 }
753 assert(0 && "unknown display type"); /* no llvm_unreachable in C. */
754 /* Set to NULL to prevent uninitialized variable warnings. */
755 text.data = NULL;
756 text.private_flags = 0;
757 return text;
758}
759
760static void PrintCursor(CXCursor Cursor, const char *CommentSchemaFile) {
761 CXTranslationUnit TU = clang_Cursor_getTranslationUnit(Cursor);
762 if (clang_isInvalid(Cursor.kind)) {
763 CXString ks = clang_getCursorKindSpelling(Cursor.kind);
764 printf("Invalid Cursor => %s", clang_getCString(ks));
765 clang_disposeString(ks);
766 }
767 else {
768 CXString string, ks;
769 CXCursor Referenced;
770 unsigned line, column;
771 CXCursor SpecializationOf;
772 CXCursor *overridden;
773 unsigned num_overridden;
774 unsigned RefNameRangeNr;
775 CXSourceRange CursorExtent;
776 CXSourceRange RefNameRange;
777 int AlwaysUnavailable;
778 int AlwaysDeprecated;
779 CXString UnavailableMessage;
780 CXString DeprecatedMessage;
781 CXPlatformAvailability PlatformAvailability[2];
782 int NumPlatformAvailability;
783 int I;
784
785 ks = clang_getCursorKindSpelling(Cursor.kind);
786 string = CursorToText(Cursor);
787 printf("%s=%s", clang_getCString(ks),
788 clang_getCString(string));
789 clang_disposeString(ks);
790 clang_disposeString(string);
791
792 Referenced = clang_getCursorReferenced(Cursor);
793 if (!clang_equalCursors(Referenced, clang_getNullCursor())) {
794 if (clang_getCursorKind(Referenced) == CXCursor_OverloadedDeclRef) {
795 unsigned I, N = clang_getNumOverloadedDecls(Referenced);
796 printf("[");
797 for (I = 0; I != N; ++I) {
798 CXCursor Ovl = clang_getOverloadedDecl(Referenced, I);
799 CXSourceLocation Loc;
800 if (I)
801 printf(", ");
802
803 Loc = clang_getCursorLocation(Ovl);
804 clang_getSpellingLocation(Loc, 0, &line, &column, 0);
805 printf("%d:%d", line, column);
806 }
807 printf("]");
808 } else {
809 CXSourceLocation Loc = clang_getCursorLocation(Referenced);
810 clang_getSpellingLocation(Loc, 0, &line, &column, 0);
811 printf(":%d:%d", line, column);
812 }
813
814 if (clang_getCursorKind(Referenced) == CXCursor_TypedefDecl) {
815 CXType T = clang_getCursorType(Referenced);
816 if (clang_Type_isTransparentTagTypedef(T)) {
817 CXType Underlying = clang_getTypedefDeclUnderlyingType(Referenced);
818 CXString S = clang_getTypeSpelling(Underlying);
819 printf(" (Transparent: %s)", clang_getCString(S));
820 clang_disposeString(S);
821 }
822 }
823 }
824
825 if (clang_isCursorDefinition(Cursor))
826 printf(" (Definition)");
827
828 switch (clang_getCursorAvailability(Cursor)) {
829 case CXAvailability_Available:
830 break;
831
832 case CXAvailability_Deprecated:
833 printf(" (deprecated)");
834 break;
835
836 case CXAvailability_NotAvailable:
837 printf(" (unavailable)");
838 break;
839
840 case CXAvailability_NotAccessible:
841 printf(" (inaccessible)");
842 break;
843 }
844
845 NumPlatformAvailability
846 = clang_getCursorPlatformAvailability(Cursor,
847 &AlwaysDeprecated,
848 &DeprecatedMessage,
849 &AlwaysUnavailable,
850 &UnavailableMessage,
851 PlatformAvailability, 2);
852 if (AlwaysUnavailable) {
853 printf(" (always unavailable: \"%s\")",
854 clang_getCString(UnavailableMessage));
855 } else if (AlwaysDeprecated) {
856 printf(" (always deprecated: \"%s\")",
857 clang_getCString(DeprecatedMessage));
858 } else {
859 for (I = 0; I != NumPlatformAvailability; ++I) {
860 if (I >= 2)
861 break;
862
863 printf(" (%s", clang_getCString(PlatformAvailability[I].Platform));
864 if (PlatformAvailability[I].Unavailable)
865 printf(", unavailable");
866 else {
867 printVersion(", introduced=", PlatformAvailability[I].Introduced);
868 printVersion(", deprecated=", PlatformAvailability[I].Deprecated);
869 printVersion(", obsoleted=", PlatformAvailability[I].Obsoleted);
870 }
871 if (clang_getCString(PlatformAvailability[I].Message)[0])
872 printf(", message=\"%s\"",
873 clang_getCString(PlatformAvailability[I].Message));
874 printf(")");
875 }
876 }
877 for (I = 0; I != NumPlatformAvailability; ++I) {
878 if (I >= 2)
879 break;
880 clang_disposeCXPlatformAvailability(PlatformAvailability + I);
881 }
882
883 clang_disposeString(DeprecatedMessage);
884 clang_disposeString(UnavailableMessage);
885
886 if (clang_CXXConstructor_isDefaultConstructor(Cursor))
887 printf(" (default constructor)");
888
889 if (clang_CXXConstructor_isMoveConstructor(Cursor))
890 printf(" (move constructor)");
891 if (clang_CXXConstructor_isCopyConstructor(Cursor))
892 printf(" (copy constructor)");
893 if (clang_CXXConstructor_isConvertingConstructor(Cursor))
894 printf(" (converting constructor)");
895 if (clang_CXXField_isMutable(Cursor))
896 printf(" (mutable)");
897 if (clang_CXXMethod_isDefaulted(Cursor))
898 printf(" (defaulted)");
899 if (clang_CXXMethod_isStatic(Cursor))
900 printf(" (static)");
901 if (clang_CXXMethod_isVirtual(Cursor))
902 printf(" (virtual)");
903 if (clang_CXXMethod_isConst(Cursor))
904 printf(" (const)");
905 if (clang_CXXMethod_isPureVirtual(Cursor))
906 printf(" (pure)");
907 if (clang_CXXRecord_isAbstract(Cursor))
908 printf(" (abstract)");
909 if (clang_EnumDecl_isScoped(Cursor))
910 printf(" (scoped)");
911 if (clang_Cursor_isVariadic(Cursor))
912 printf(" (variadic)");
913 if (clang_Cursor_isObjCOptional(Cursor))
914 printf(" (@optional)");
915 if (clang_isInvalidDeclaration(Cursor))
916 printf(" (invalid)");
917
918 switch (clang_getCursorExceptionSpecificationType(Cursor))
919 {
920 case CXCursor_ExceptionSpecificationKind_None:
921 break;
922
923 case CXCursor_ExceptionSpecificationKind_DynamicNone:
924 printf(" (noexcept dynamic none)");
925 break;
926
927 case CXCursor_ExceptionSpecificationKind_Dynamic:
928 printf(" (noexcept dynamic)");
929 break;
930
931 case CXCursor_ExceptionSpecificationKind_MSAny:
932 printf(" (noexcept dynamic any)");
933 break;
934
935 case CXCursor_ExceptionSpecificationKind_BasicNoexcept:
936 printf(" (noexcept)");
937 break;
938
939 case CXCursor_ExceptionSpecificationKind_ComputedNoexcept:
940 printf(" (computed-noexcept)");
941 break;
942
943 case CXCursor_ExceptionSpecificationKind_Unevaluated:
944 case CXCursor_ExceptionSpecificationKind_Uninstantiated:
945 case CXCursor_ExceptionSpecificationKind_Unparsed:
946 break;
947 }
948
949 {
950 CXString language;
951 CXString definedIn;
952 unsigned generated;
953 if (clang_Cursor_isExternalSymbol(Cursor, &language, &definedIn,
954 &generated)) {
955 printf(" (external lang: %s, defined: %s, gen: %d)",
956 clang_getCString(language), clang_getCString(definedIn), generated);
957 clang_disposeString(language);
958 clang_disposeString(definedIn);
959 }
960 }
961
962 if (Cursor.kind == CXCursor_IBOutletCollectionAttr) {
963 CXType T =
964 clang_getCanonicalType(clang_getIBOutletCollectionType(Cursor));
965 CXString S = clang_getTypeKindSpelling(T.kind);
966 printf(" [IBOutletCollection=%s]", clang_getCString(S));
967 clang_disposeString(S);
968 }
969
970 if (Cursor.kind == CXCursor_CXXBaseSpecifier) {
971 enum CX_CXXAccessSpecifier access = clang_getCXXAccessSpecifier(Cursor);
972 unsigned isVirtual = clang_isVirtualBase(Cursor);
973 const char *accessStr = 0;
974
975 switch (access) {
976 case CX_CXXInvalidAccessSpecifier:
977 accessStr = "invalid"; break;
978 case CX_CXXPublic:
979 accessStr = "public"; break;
980 case CX_CXXProtected:
981 accessStr = "protected"; break;
982 case CX_CXXPrivate:
983 accessStr = "private"; break;
984 }
985
986 printf(" [access=%s isVirtual=%s]", accessStr,
987 isVirtual ? "true" : "false");
988 }
989
990 SpecializationOf = clang_getSpecializedCursorTemplate(Cursor);
991 if (!clang_equalCursors(SpecializationOf, clang_getNullCursor())) {
992 CXSourceLocation Loc = clang_getCursorLocation(SpecializationOf);
993 CXString Name = clang_getCursorSpelling(SpecializationOf);
994 clang_getSpellingLocation(Loc, 0, &line, &column, 0);
995 printf(" [Specialization of %s:%d:%d]",
996 clang_getCString(Name), line, column);
997 clang_disposeString(Name);
998
999 if (Cursor.kind == CXCursor_FunctionDecl) {
1000 /* Collect the template parameter kinds from the base template. */
1001 int NumTemplateArgs = clang_Cursor_getNumTemplateArguments(Cursor);
1002 int I;
1003 if (NumTemplateArgs < 0) {
1004 printf(" [no template arg info]");
1005 }
1006 for (I = 0; I < NumTemplateArgs; I++) {
1007 enum CXTemplateArgumentKind TAK =
1008 clang_Cursor_getTemplateArgumentKind(Cursor, I);
1009 switch(TAK) {
1010 case CXTemplateArgumentKind_Type:
1011 {
1012 CXType T = clang_Cursor_getTemplateArgumentType(Cursor, I);
1013 CXString S = clang_getTypeSpelling(T);
1014 printf(" [Template arg %d: kind: %d, type: %s]",
1015 I, TAK, clang_getCString(S));
1016 clang_disposeString(S);
1017 }
1018 break;
1019 case CXTemplateArgumentKind_Integral:
1020 printf(" [Template arg %d: kind: %d, intval: %lld]",
1021 I, TAK, clang_Cursor_getTemplateArgumentValue(Cursor, I));
1022 break;
1023 default:
1024 printf(" [Template arg %d: kind: %d]\n", I, TAK);
1025 }
1026 }
1027 }
1028 }
1029
1030 clang_getOverriddenCursors(Cursor, &overridden, &num_overridden);
1031 if (num_overridden) {
1032 unsigned I;
1033 LineCol lineCols[50];
1034 assert(num_overridden <= 50);
1035 printf(" [Overrides ");
1036 for (I = 0; I != num_overridden; ++I) {
1037 CXSourceLocation Loc = clang_getCursorLocation(overridden[I]);
1038 clang_getSpellingLocation(Loc, 0, &line, &column, 0);
1039 lineCols[I].line = line;
1040 lineCols[I].col = column;
1041 }
1042 /* Make the order of the override list deterministic. */
1043 qsort(lineCols, num_overridden, sizeof(LineCol), lineCol_cmp);
1044 for (I = 0; I != num_overridden; ++I) {
1045 if (I)
1046 printf(", ");
1047 printf("@%d:%d", lineCols[I].line, lineCols[I].col);
1048 }
1049 printf("]");
1050 clang_disposeOverriddenCursors(overridden);
1051 }
1052
1053 if (Cursor.kind == CXCursor_InclusionDirective) {
1054 CXFile File = clang_getIncludedFile(Cursor);
1055 CXString Included = clang_getFileName(File);
1056 printf(" (%s)", clang_getCString(Included));
1057 clang_disposeString(Included);
1058
1059 if (clang_isFileMultipleIncludeGuarded(TU, File))
1060 printf(" [multi-include guarded]");
1061 }
1062
1063 CursorExtent = clang_getCursorExtent(Cursor);
1064 RefNameRange = clang_getCursorReferenceNameRange(Cursor,
1065 CXNameRange_WantQualifier
1066 | CXNameRange_WantSinglePiece
1067 | CXNameRange_WantTemplateArgs,
1068 0);
1069 if (!clang_equalRanges(CursorExtent, RefNameRange))
1070 PrintRange(RefNameRange, "SingleRefName");
1071
1072 for (RefNameRangeNr = 0; 1; RefNameRangeNr++) {
1073 RefNameRange = clang_getCursorReferenceNameRange(Cursor,
1074 CXNameRange_WantQualifier
1075 | CXNameRange_WantTemplateArgs,
1076 RefNameRangeNr);
1077 if (clang_equalRanges(clang_getNullRange(), RefNameRange))
1078 break;
1079 if (!clang_equalRanges(CursorExtent, RefNameRange))
1080 PrintRange(RefNameRange, "RefName");
1081 }
1082
1083 PrintCursorComments(Cursor, CommentSchemaFile);
1084
1085 {
1086 unsigned PropAttrs = clang_Cursor_getObjCPropertyAttributes(Cursor, 0);
1087 if (PropAttrs != CXObjCPropertyAttr_noattr) {
1088 printf(" [");
1089 #define PRINT_PROP_ATTR(A) \
1090 if (PropAttrs & CXObjCPropertyAttr_##A) printf(#A ",")
1091 PRINT_PROP_ATTR(readonly);
1092 PRINT_PROP_ATTR(getter);
1093 PRINT_PROP_ATTR(assign);
1094 PRINT_PROP_ATTR(readwrite);
1095 PRINT_PROP_ATTR(retain);
1096 PRINT_PROP_ATTR(copy);
1097 PRINT_PROP_ATTR(nonatomic);
1098 PRINT_PROP_ATTR(setter);
1099 PRINT_PROP_ATTR(atomic);
1100 PRINT_PROP_ATTR(weak);
1101 PRINT_PROP_ATTR(strong);
1102 PRINT_PROP_ATTR(unsafe_unretained);
1103 PRINT_PROP_ATTR(class);
1104 printf("]");
1105 }
1106 }
1107
1108 if (Cursor.kind == CXCursor_ObjCPropertyDecl) {
1109 CXString Name = clang_Cursor_getObjCPropertyGetterName(Cursor);
1110 CXString Spelling = clang_getCursorSpelling(Cursor);
1111 const char *CName = clang_getCString(Name);
1112 const char *CSpelling = clang_getCString(Spelling);
1113 if (CName && strcmp(CName, CSpelling)) {
1114 printf(" (getter=%s)", CName);
1115 }
1116 clang_disposeString(Spelling);
1117 clang_disposeString(Name);
1118 }
1119
1120 if (Cursor.kind == CXCursor_ObjCPropertyDecl) {
1121 CXString Name = clang_Cursor_getObjCPropertySetterName(Cursor);
1122 CXString Spelling = clang_getCursorSpelling(Cursor);
1123 const char *CName = clang_getCString(Name);
1124 const char *CSpelling = clang_getCString(Spelling);
1125 char *DefaultSetter = malloc(strlen(CSpelling) + 5);
1126 sprintf(DefaultSetter, "set%s:", CSpelling);
1127 DefaultSetter[3] &= ~(1 << 5); /* Make uppercase */
1128 if (CName && strcmp(CName, DefaultSetter)) {
1129 printf(" (setter=%s)", CName);
1130 }
1131 free(DefaultSetter);
1132 clang_disposeString(Spelling);
1133 clang_disposeString(Name);
1134 }
1135
1136 {
1137 unsigned QT = clang_Cursor_getObjCDeclQualifiers(Cursor);
1138 if (QT != CXObjCDeclQualifier_None) {
1139 printf(" [");
1140 #define PRINT_OBJC_QUAL(A) \
1141 if (QT & CXObjCDeclQualifier_##A) printf(#A ",")
1142 PRINT_OBJC_QUAL(In);
1143 PRINT_OBJC_QUAL(Inout);
1144 PRINT_OBJC_QUAL(Out);
1145 PRINT_OBJC_QUAL(Bycopy);
1146 PRINT_OBJC_QUAL(Byref);
1147 PRINT_OBJC_QUAL(Oneway);
1148 printf("]");
1149 }
1150 }
1151 }
1152}

1154static const char* GetCursorSource(CXCursor Cursor) {
1155 CXSourceLocation Loc = clang_getCursorLocation(Cursor);
1156 CXString source;
1157 CXFile file;
1158 clang_getExpansionLocation(Loc, &file, 0, 0, 0);
1159 source = clang_getFileName(file);
1160 if (!clang_getCString(source)) {
1161 clang_disposeString(source);
1162 return "<invalid loc>";
1163 }
1164 else {
1165 const char *b = basename(clang_getCString(source));
1166 clang_disposeString(source);
1167 return b;
1168 }
1169}

1172 CXString Str;
1173 Str.data = (const void *) CS;
1174 Str.private_flags = 0;
1175 return Str;
1176}

1183
1184void PrintDiagnostic(CXDiagnostic Diagnostic) {
1185 FILE *out = stderr;
1186 CXFile file;
1187 CXString Msg;
1188 unsigned display_opts = CXDiagnostic_DisplaySourceLocation
1189 | CXDiagnostic_DisplayColumn | CXDiagnostic_DisplaySourceRanges
1190 | CXDiagnostic_DisplayOption;
1191 unsigned i, num_fixits;
1192
1193 if (clang_getDiagnosticSeverity(Diagnostic) == CXDiagnostic_Ignored)
1194 return;
1195
1196 Msg = clang_formatDiagnostic(Diagnostic, display_opts);
1197 fprintf(stderr, "%s\n", clang_getCString(Msg));
1198 clang_disposeString(Msg);
1199
1200 clang_getSpellingLocation(clang_getDiagnosticLocation(Diagnostic),
1201 &file, 0, 0, 0);
1202 if (!file)
1203 return;
1204
1205 num_fixits = clang_getDiagnosticNumFixIts(Diagnostic);
1206 fprintf(stderr, "Number FIX-ITs = %d\n", num_fixits);
1207 for (i = 0; i != num_fixits; ++i) {
1208 CXSourceRange range;
1209 CXString insertion_text = clang_getDiagnosticFixIt(Diagnostic, i, &range);
1210 CXSourceLocation start = clang_getRangeStart(range);
1211 CXSourceLocation end = clang_getRangeEnd(range);
1212 unsigned start_line, start_column, end_line, end_column;
1213 CXFile start_file, end_file;
1214 clang_getSpellingLocation(start, &start_file, &start_line,
1215 &start_column, 0);
1216 clang_getSpellingLocation(end, &end_file, &end_line, &end_column, 0);
1217 if (clang_equalLocations(start, end)) {
1218 /* Insertion. */
1219 if (start_file == file)
1220 fprintf(out, "FIX-IT: Insert \"%s\" at %d:%d\n",
1221 clang_getCString(insertion_text), start_line, start_column);
1222 } else if (strcmp(clang_getCString(insertion_text), "") == 0) {
1223 /* Removal. */
1224 if (start_file == file && end_file == file) {
1225 fprintf(out, "FIX-IT: Remove ");
1226 PrintExtent(out, start_line, start_column, end_line, end_column);
1227 fprintf(out, "\n");
1228 }
1229 } else {
1230 /* Replacement. */
1231 if (start_file == end_file) {
1232 fprintf(out, "FIX-IT: Replace ");
1233 PrintExtent(out, start_line, start_column, end_line, end_column);
1234 fprintf(out, " with \"%s\"\n", clang_getCString(insertion_text));
1235 }
1236 }
1237 clang_disposeString(insertion_text);
1238 }
1239}

1241void PrintDiagnosticSet(CXDiagnosticSet Set) {
1242 int i = 0, n = clang_getNumDiagnosticsInSet(Set);
1243 for ( ; i != n ; ++i) {
1244 CXDiagnostic Diag = clang_getDiagnosticInSet(Set, i);
1245 CXDiagnosticSet ChildDiags = clang_getChildDiagnostics(Diag);
1246 PrintDiagnostic(Diag);
1247 if (ChildDiags)
1248 PrintDiagnosticSet(ChildDiags);
1249 }

1258void PrintMemoryUsage(CXTranslationUnit TU) {
1259 unsigned long total = 0;
1260 unsigned i = 0;
1261 CXTUResourceUsage usage = clang_getCXTUResourceUsage(TU);
1262 fprintf(stderr, "Memory usage:\n");
1263 for (i = 0 ; i != usage.numEntries; ++i) {
1264 const char *name = clang_getTUResourceUsageName(usage.entries[i].kind);
1265 unsigned long amount = usage.entries[i].amount;
1266 total += amount;
1267 fprintf(stderr, " %s : %ld bytes (%f MBytes)\n", name, amount,
1268 ((double) amount)/(1024*1024));
1269 }
1270 fprintf(stderr, " TOTAL = %ld bytes (%f MBytes)\n", total,
1271 ((double) total)/(1024*1024));
1272 clang_disposeCXTUResourceUsage(usage);
1273}

1284/* Data used by the visitors. */
1285typedef struct {
1286 CXTranslationUnit TU;
1287 enum CXCursorKind *Filter;
1288 const char *CommentSchemaFile;
1289} VisitorData;
1290
1291
1292enum CXChildVisitResult FilteredPrintingVisitor(CXCursor Cursor,
1293 CXCursor Parent,
1294 CXClientData ClientData) {
1295 VisitorData *Data = (VisitorData *)ClientData;
1296 if (!Data->Filter || (Cursor.kind == *(enum CXCursorKind *)Data->Filter)) {
1297 CXSourceLocation Loc = clang_getCursorLocation(Cursor);
1298 unsigned line, column;
1299 clang_getSpellingLocation(Loc, 0, &line, &column, 0);
1300 printf("// %s: %s:%d:%d: ", FileCheckPrefix,
1301 GetCursorSource(Cursor), line, column);
1302 PrintCursor(Cursor, Data->CommentSchemaFile);
1303 PrintCursorExtent(Cursor);
1304 if (clang_isDeclaration(Cursor.kind)) {
1305 enum CX_CXXAccessSpecifier access = clang_getCXXAccessSpecifier(Cursor);
1306 const char *accessStr = 0;
1307
1308 switch (access) {
1309 case CX_CXXInvalidAccessSpecifier: break;
1310 case CX_CXXPublic:
1311 accessStr = "public"; break;
1312 case CX_CXXProtected:
1313 accessStr = "protected"; break;
1314 case CX_CXXPrivate:
1315 accessStr = "private"; break;
1316 }
1317
1318 if (accessStr)
1319 printf(" [access=%s]", accessStr);
1320 }
1321 printf("\n");
1322 return CXChildVisit_Recurse;
1323 }
1324
1325 return CXChildVisit_Continue;
1326}
1327
1328static enum CXChildVisitResult FunctionScanVisitor(CXCursor Cursor,
1329 CXCursor Parent,
1330 CXClientData ClientData) {
1331 const char *startBuf, *endBuf;
1332 unsigned startLine, startColumn, endLine, endColumn, curLine, curColumn;
1333 CXCursor Ref;
1334 VisitorData *Data = (VisitorData *)ClientData;
1335
1336 if (Cursor.kind != CXCursor_FunctionDecl ||
1337 !clang_isCursorDefinition(Cursor))
1338 return CXChildVisit_Continue;
1339
1340 clang_getDefinitionSpellingAndExtent(Cursor, &startBuf, &endBuf,
1341 &startLine, &startColumn,
1342 &endLine, &endColumn);
1343 /* Probe the entire body, looking for both decls and refs. */
1344 curLine = startLine;
1345 curColumn = startColumn;
1346
1347 while (startBuf < endBuf) {
1348 CXSourceLocation Loc;
1349 CXFile file;
1350 CXString source;
1351
1352 if (*startBuf == '\n') {
1353 startBuf++;
1354 curLine++;
1355 curColumn = 1;
1356 } else if (*startBuf != '\t')
1357 curColumn++;
1358
1359 Loc = clang_getCursorLocation(Cursor);
1360 clang_getSpellingLocation(Loc, &file, 0, 0, 0);
1361
1362 source = clang_getFileName(file);
1363 if (clang_getCString(source)) {
1364 CXSourceLocation RefLoc
1365 = clang_getLocation(Data->TU, file, curLine, curColumn);
1366 Ref = clang_getCursor(Data->TU, RefLoc);
1367 if (Ref.kind == CXCursor_NoDeclFound) {
1368 /* Nothing found here; that's fine. */
1369 } else if (Ref.kind != CXCursor_FunctionDecl) {
1370 printf("// %s: %s:%d:%d: ", FileCheckPrefix, GetCursorSource(Ref),
1371 curLine, curColumn);
1372 PrintCursor(Ref, Data->CommentSchemaFile);
1373 printf("\n");
1374 }
1375 }
1376 clang_disposeString(source);
1377 startBuf++;
1378 }
1379
1380 return CXChildVisit_Continue;
1381}

1383/******************************************************************************/
1384/* USR testing. */
1385/******************************************************************************/
1386
1387enum CXChildVisitResult USRVisitor(CXCursor C, CXCursor parent,
1388 CXClientData ClientData) {
1389 VisitorData *Data = (VisitorData *)ClientData;
1390 if (!Data->Filter || (C.kind == *(enum CXCursorKind *)Data->Filter)) {
1391 CXString USR = clang_getCursorUSR(C);
1392 const char *cstr = clang_getCString(USR);
1393 if (!cstr || cstr[0] == '\0') {
1394 clang_disposeString(USR);
1395 return CXChildVisit_Recurse;
1396 }
1397 printf("// %s: %s %s", FileCheckPrefix, GetCursorSource(C), cstr);
1398
1399 PrintCursorExtent(C);
1400 printf("\n");
1401 clang_disposeString(USR);
1402
1403 return CXChildVisit_Recurse;
1404 }
1405
1406 return CXChildVisit_Continue;
1407}

1413void InclusionVisitor(CXFile includedFile, CXSourceLocation *includeStack,

1419 fname = clang_getFileName(includedFile);

1429 printf(" %s:%d:%d\n", clang_getCString(fname), line, column);
1430 clang_disposeString(fname);
1431 }
1432 printf("\n");
1433}

1514static void PrintTypeTemplateArgs(CXType T, const char *Format) {
1515 int NumTArgs = clang_Type_getNumTemplateArguments(T);
1516 if (NumTArgs != -1 && NumTArgs != 0) {
1517 int i;
1518 CXType TArg;
1519 printf(Format, NumTArgs);
1520 for (i = 0; i < NumTArgs; ++i) {
1521 TArg = clang_Type_getTemplateArgumentAsType(T, i);
1522 if (TArg.kind != CXType_Invalid) {
1523 PrintTypeAndTypeKind(TArg, " [type=%s] [typekind=%s]");
1524 }
1525 }
1526 /* Ensure that the returned type is invalid when indexing off-by-one. */
1527 TArg = clang_Type_getTemplateArgumentAsType(T, i);
1528 assert(TArg.kind == CXType_Invalid);
1529 printf("]");
1530 }
1531}

1533static void PrintNullabilityKind(CXType T, const char *Format) {
1534 enum CXTypeNullabilityKind N = clang_Type_getNullability(T);
1535
1536 const char *nullability = 0;
1537 switch (N) {
1538 case CXTypeNullability_NonNull: nullability = "nonnull"; break;
1539 case CXTypeNullability_Nullable: nullability = "nullable"; break;
1540 case CXTypeNullability_Unspecified: nullability = "unspecified"; break;
1541 case CXTypeNullability_Invalid: break;
1542 }
1543
1544 if (nullability) {
1545 printf(Format, nullability);
1546 }
1547}

1549static enum CXChildVisitResult PrintType(CXCursor cursor, CXCursor p,
1550 CXClientData d) {
1551 if (!clang_isInvalid(clang_getCursorKind(cursor))) {
1552 CXType T = clang_getCursorType(cursor);
1553 CXType PT = clang_getPointeeType(T);
1554 enum CXRefQualifierKind RQ = clang_Type_getCXXRefQualifier(T);
1555 PrintCursor(cursor, NULL);
1556 PrintTypeAndTypeKind(T, " [type=%s] [typekind=%s]");
1557 PrintNullabilityKind(T, " [nullability=%s]");
1558 if (clang_isConstQualifiedType(T))
1559 printf(" const");
1560 if (clang_isVolatileQualifiedType(T))
1561 printf(" volatile");
1562 if (clang_isRestrictQualifiedType(T))
1563 printf(" restrict");
1564 if (RQ == CXRefQualifier_LValue)
1565 printf(" lvalue-ref-qualifier");
1566 if (RQ == CXRefQualifier_RValue)
1567 printf(" rvalue-ref-qualifier");
1568 /* Print the template argument types if they exist. */
1569 PrintTypeTemplateArgs(T, " [templateargs/%d=");
1570 /* Print the canonical type if it is different. */
1571 {
1572 CXType CT = clang_getCanonicalType(T);
1573 if (!clang_equalTypes(T, CT)) {
1574 PrintTypeAndTypeKind(CT, " [canonicaltype=%s] [canonicaltypekind=%s]");
1575 PrintTypeTemplateArgs(CT, " [canonicaltemplateargs/%d=");
1576 }
1577 }
1578 /* Print the modified type if it exists. */
1579 {
1580 CXType MT = clang_Type_getModifiedType(T);
1581 if (MT.kind != CXType_Invalid) {
1582 PrintTypeAndTypeKind(MT, " [modifiedtype=%s] [modifiedtypekind=%s]");
1583 }
1584 }
1585 /* Print the return type if it exists. */
1586 {
1587 CXType RT = clang_getCursorResultType(cursor);
1588 if (RT.kind != CXType_Invalid) {
1589 PrintTypeAndTypeKind(RT, " [resulttype=%s] [resulttypekind=%s]");
1590 }
1591 PrintNullabilityKind(RT, " [resultnullability=%s]");
1592 }
1593 /* Print the argument types if they exist. */
1594 {
1595 int NumArgs = clang_Cursor_getNumArguments(cursor);
1596 if (NumArgs != -1 && NumArgs != 0) {
1597 int i;
1598 printf(" [args=");
1599 for (i = 0; i < NumArgs; ++i) {
1600 CXType T = clang_getCursorType(clang_Cursor_getArgument(cursor, i));
1601 if (T.kind != CXType_Invalid) {
1602 PrintTypeAndTypeKind(T, " [%s] [%s]");
1603 PrintNullabilityKind(T, " [%s]");
1604 }
1605 }
1606 printf("]");
1607 }
1608 }
1609 /* Print ObjC base types, type arguments, and protocol list if available. */
1610 {
1611 CXType BT = clang_Type_getObjCObjectBaseType(PT);
1612 if (BT.kind != CXType_Invalid) {
1613 PrintTypeAndTypeKind(BT, " [basetype=%s] [basekind=%s]");
1614 }
1615 }
1616 {
1617 unsigned NumTypeArgs = clang_Type_getNumObjCTypeArgs(PT);
1618 if (NumTypeArgs > 0) {
1619 unsigned i;
1620 printf(" [typeargs=");
1621 for (i = 0; i < NumTypeArgs; ++i) {
1622 CXType TA = clang_Type_getObjCTypeArg(PT, i);
1623 if (TA.kind != CXType_Invalid) {
1624 PrintTypeAndTypeKind(TA, " [%s] [%s]");
1625 }
1626 }
1627 printf("]");
1628 }
1629 }
1630 {
1631 unsigned NumProtocols = clang_Type_getNumObjCProtocolRefs(PT);
1632 if (NumProtocols > 0) {
1633 unsigned i;
1634 printf(" [protocols=");
1635 for (i = 0; i < NumProtocols; ++i) {
1636 CXCursor P = clang_Type_getObjCProtocolDecl(PT, i);
1637 if (!clang_isInvalid(clang_getCursorKind(P))) {
1638 PrintCursor(P, NULL);
1639 }
1640 }
1641 printf("]");
1642 }
1643 }
1644 /* Print if this is a non-POD type. */
1645 printf(" [isPOD=%d]", clang_isPODType(T));
1646 /* Print the pointee type. */
1647 {
1648 if (PT.kind != CXType_Invalid) {
1649 PrintTypeAndTypeKind(PT, " [pointeetype=%s] [pointeekind=%s]");
1650 }
1651 }
1652 /* Print the number of fields if they exist. */
1653 {
1654 int numFields = 0;
1655 if (clang_Type_visitFields(T, FieldVisitor, &numFields)){
1656 if (numFields != 0) {
1657 printf(" [nbFields=%d]", numFields);
1658 }
1659 }
1660 }
1661
1662 /* Print if it is an anonymous record or namespace. */
1663 {
1664 unsigned isAnon = clang_Cursor_isAnonymous(cursor);
1665 if (isAnon != 0) {
1666 printf(" [isAnon=%d]", isAnon);
1667 }
1668 }
1669
1670 /* Print if it is an anonymous record decl */
1671 {
1672 unsigned isAnonRecDecl = clang_Cursor_isAnonymousRecordDecl(cursor);
1673 printf(" [isAnonRecDecl=%d]", isAnonRecDecl);
1674 }
1675
1676 /* Print if it is an inline namespace decl */
1677 {
1678 unsigned isInlineNamespace = clang_Cursor_isInlineNamespace(cursor);
1679 if (isInlineNamespace != 0)
1680 printf(" [isInlineNamespace=%d]", isInlineNamespace);
1681 }
1682
1683 printf("\n");
1684 }
1685 return CXChildVisit_Recurse;
1686}

1688static void PrintSingleTypeSize(CXType T, const char *TypeKindFormat,
1689 const char *SizeFormat,
1690 const char *AlignFormat) {
1691 PrintTypeAndTypeKind(T, TypeKindFormat);
1692 /* Print the type sizeof if applicable. */
1693 {
1694 long long Size = clang_Type_getSizeOf(T);
1695 if (Size >= 0 || Size < -1 ) {
1696 printf(SizeFormat, Size);
1697 }
1698 }
1699 /* Print the type alignof if applicable. */
1700 {
1701 long long Align = clang_Type_getAlignOf(T);
1702 if (Align >= 0 || Align < -1) {
1703 printf(AlignFormat, Align);
1704 }
1705 }
1706
1707 /* Print the return type if it exists. */
1708 {
1709 CXType RT = clang_getResultType(T);
1710 if (RT.kind != CXType_Invalid)
1711 PrintSingleTypeSize(RT, " [resulttype=%s] [resulttypekind=%s]",
1712 " [resultsizeof=%lld]", " [resultalignof=%lld]");
1713 }
1714}
1715
1716static enum CXChildVisitResult PrintTypeSize(CXCursor cursor, CXCursor p,
1717 CXClientData d) {
1718 CXType T;
1719 enum CXCursorKind K = clang_getCursorKind(cursor);
1720 if (clang_isInvalid(K))
1721 return CXChildVisit_Recurse;
1722 T = clang_getCursorType(cursor);
1723 PrintCursor(cursor, NULL);
1724 PrintSingleTypeSize(T, " [type=%s] [typekind=%s]", " [sizeof=%lld]",
1725 " [alignof=%lld]");
1726 /* Print the record field offset if applicable. */
1727 {
1728 CXString FieldSpelling = clang_getCursorSpelling(cursor);
1729 const char *FieldName = clang_getCString(FieldSpelling);
1730 /* recurse to get the first parent record that is not anonymous. */
1731 unsigned RecordIsAnonymous = 0;
1732 if (clang_getCursorKind(cursor) == CXCursor_FieldDecl) {
1733 CXCursor Record;
1734 CXCursor Parent = p;
1735 do {
1736 Record = Parent;
1737 Parent = clang_getCursorSemanticParent(Record);
1738 RecordIsAnonymous = clang_Cursor_isAnonymous(Record);
1739 /* Recurse as long as the parent is a CXType_Record and the Record
1740 is anonymous */
1741 } while ( clang_getCursorType(Parent).kind == CXType_Record &&
1742 RecordIsAnonymous > 0);
1743 {
1744 long long Offset = clang_Type_getOffsetOf(clang_getCursorType(Record),
1745 FieldName);
1746 long long Offset2 = clang_Cursor_getOffsetOfField(cursor);
1747 if (Offset == Offset2){
1748 printf(" [offsetof=%lld]", Offset);
1749 } else {
1750 /* Offsets will be different in anonymous records. */
1751 printf(" [offsetof=%lld/%lld]", Offset, Offset2);
1752 }
1753 }
1754 }
1755 clang_disposeString(FieldSpelling);
1756 }
1757 /* Print if its a bitfield */
1758 {
1759 int IsBitfield = clang_Cursor_isBitField(cursor);
1760 if (IsBitfield)
1761 printf(" [BitFieldSize=%d]", clang_getFieldDeclBitWidth(cursor));
1762 }
1763
1764 printf("\n");
1765
1766 return CXChildVisit_Recurse;
1767}

1865/******************************************************************************/
1866/* Target information testing. */
1867/******************************************************************************/
1868
1869static int print_target_info(int argc, const char **argv) {
1870 CXIndex Idx;
1871 CXTranslationUnit TU;
1872 CXTargetInfo TargetInfo;
1873 CXString Triple;
1874 const char *FileName;
1875 enum CXErrorCode Err;
1876 int PointerWidth;
1877
1878 if (argc == 0) {
1879 fprintf(stderr, "No filename specified\n");
1880 return 1;
1881 }
1882
1883 FileName = argv[1];
1884
1885 Idx = clang_createIndex(0, 1);
1886 Err = clang_parseTranslationUnit2(Idx, FileName, argv, argc, NULL, 0,
1887 getDefaultParsingOptions(), &TU);
1888 if (Err != CXError_Success) {
1889 fprintf(stderr, "Couldn't parse translation unit!\n");
1890 describeLibclangFailure(Err);
1891 clang_disposeIndex(Idx);
1892 return 1;
1893 }
1894
1895 TargetInfo = clang_getTranslationUnitTargetInfo(TU);
1896
1897 Triple = clang_TargetInfo_getTriple(TargetInfo);
1898 printf("TargetTriple: %s\n", clang_getCString(Triple));
1899 clang_disposeString(Triple);
1900
1901 PointerWidth = clang_TargetInfo_getPointerWidth(TargetInfo);
1902 printf("PointerWidth: %d\n", PointerWidth);
1903
1904 clang_TargetInfo_dispose(TargetInfo);
1905 clang_disposeTranslationUnit(TU);
1906 clang_disposeIndex(Idx);
1907 return 0;
1908}

1910/******************************************************************************/
1911/* Loading ASTs/source. */
1912/******************************************************************************/
1913
1914static int perform_test_load(CXIndex Idx, CXTranslationUnit TU,
1915 const char *filter, const char *prefix,
1916 CXCursorVisitor Visitor,
1917 PostVisitTU PV,
1918 const char *CommentSchemaFile) {
1919
1920 if (prefix)
1921 FileCheckPrefix = prefix;
1922
1923 if (Visitor) {
1924 enum CXCursorKind K = CXCursor_NotImplemented;
1925 enum CXCursorKind *ck = &K;
1926 VisitorData Data;
1927
1928 /* Perform some simple filtering. */
1929 if (!strcmp(filter, "all") || !strcmp(filter, "local")) ck = NULL;
1930 else if (!strcmp(filter, "all-display") ||
1931 !strcmp(filter, "local-display")) {
1932 ck = NULL;
1933 wanted_display_type = DisplayType_DisplayName;
1934 }
1935 else if (!strcmp(filter, "all-pretty") ||
1936 !strcmp(filter, "local-pretty")) {
1937 ck = NULL;
1938 wanted_display_type = DisplayType_Pretty;
1939 }
1940 else if (!strcmp(filter, "none")) K = (enum CXCursorKind) ~0;
1941 else if (!strcmp(filter, "category")) K = CXCursor_ObjCCategoryDecl;
1942 else if (!strcmp(filter, "interface")) K = CXCursor_ObjCInterfaceDecl;
1943 else if (!strcmp(filter, "protocol")) K = CXCursor_ObjCProtocolDecl;
1944 else if (!strcmp(filter, "function")) K = CXCursor_FunctionDecl;
1945 else if (!strcmp(filter, "typedef")) K = CXCursor_TypedefDecl;
1946 else if (!strcmp(filter, "scan-function")) Visitor = FunctionScanVisitor;
1947 else {
1948 fprintf(stderr, "Unknown filter for -test-load-tu: %s\n", filter);
1949 return 1;
1950 }
1951
1952 Data.TU = TU;
1953 Data.Filter = ck;
1954 Data.CommentSchemaFile = CommentSchemaFile;
1955 clang_visitChildren(clang_getTranslationUnitCursor(TU), Visitor, &Data);
1956 }
1957
1958 if (PV)
1959 PV(TU);
1960
1961 PrintDiagnostics(TU);
1962 if (checkForErrors(TU) != 0) {
1963 clang_disposeTranslationUnit(TU);
1964 return -1;
1965 }
1966
1967 clang_disposeTranslationUnit(TU);
1968 return 0;
1969}
1970
1971int perform_test_load_tu(const char *file, const char *filter,
1972 const char *prefix, CXCursorVisitor Visitor,
1973 PostVisitTU PV) {
1974 CXIndex Idx;
1975 CXTranslationUnit TU;
1976 int result;
1977 Idx = clang_createIndex(/* excludeDeclsFromPCH */
1978 !strcmp(filter, "local") ? 1 : 0,
1979 /* displayDiagnostics=*/1);
1980
1981 if (!CreateTranslationUnit(Idx, file, &TU)) {
1982 clang_disposeIndex(Idx);
1983 return 1;
1984 }
1985
1986 result = perform_test_load(Idx, TU, filter, prefix, Visitor, PV, NULL);
1987 clang_disposeIndex(Idx);
1988 return result;
1989}
1990
1991int perform_test_load_source(int argc, const char **argv,
1992 const char *filter, CXCursorVisitor Visitor,
1993 PostVisitTU PV) {
1994 CXIndex Idx;
1995 CXTranslationUnit TU;
1996 const char *CommentSchemaFile;
1997 struct CXUnsavedFile *unsaved_files = 0;
1998 int num_unsaved_files = 0;
1999 enum CXErrorCode Err;
2000 int result;
2001 unsigned Repeats = 0;
2002 unsigned I;
2003 const char *InvocationPath;
2004
2005 Idx = clang_createIndex(/* excludeDeclsFromPCH */
2006 (!strcmp(filter, "local") ||
2007 !strcmp(filter, "local-display") ||
2008 !strcmp(filter, "local-pretty"))
2009 ? 1
2010 : 0,
2011 /* displayDiagnostics=*/1);
2012 InvocationPath = getenv("CINDEXTEST_INVOCATION_EMISSION_PATH");
2013 if (InvocationPath)
2014 clang_CXIndex_setInvocationEmissionPathOption(Idx, InvocationPath);
2015
2016 if ((CommentSchemaFile = parse_comments_schema(argc, argv))) {
2017 argc--;
2018 argv++;
2019 }
2020
2021 if (parse_remapped_files(argc, argv, 0, &unsaved_files, &num_unsaved_files)) {
2022 clang_disposeIndex(Idx);
2023 return -1;
2024 }
2025
2026 if (getenv("CINDEXTEST_EDITING"))
2027 Repeats = 5;
2028
2029 Err = clang_parseTranslationUnit2(Idx, 0,
2030 argv + num_unsaved_files,
2031 argc - num_unsaved_files,
2032 unsaved_files, num_unsaved_files,
2033 getDefaultParsingOptions(), &TU);
2034 if (Err != CXError_Success) {
2035 fprintf(stderr, "Unable to load translation unit!\n");
2036 describeLibclangFailure(Err);
2037 free_remapped_files(unsaved_files, num_unsaved_files);
2038 clang_disposeIndex(Idx);
2039 return 1;
2040 }
2041
2042 for (I = 0; I != Repeats; ++I) {
2043 if (checkForErrors(TU) != 0)
2044 return -1;
2045
2046 if (Repeats > 1) {
2047 clang_suspendTranslationUnit(TU);
2048
2049 Err = clang_reparseTranslationUnit(TU, num_unsaved_files, unsaved_files,
2050 clang_defaultReparseOptions(TU));
2051 if (Err != CXError_Success) {
2052 describeLibclangFailure(Err);
2053 free_remapped_files(unsaved_files, num_unsaved_files);
2054 clang_disposeIndex(Idx);
2055 return 1;
2056 }
2057 }
2058 }
2059
2060 result = perform_test_load(Idx, TU, filter, NULL, Visitor, PV,
2061 CommentSchemaFile);
2062 free_remapped_files(unsaved_files, num_unsaved_files);
2063 clang_disposeIndex(Idx);
2064 return result;
2065}
2066
2067int perform_test_reparse_source(int argc, const char **argv, int trials,
2068 const char *filter, CXCursorVisitor Visitor,
2069 PostVisitTU PV) {
2070 CXIndex Idx;
2071 CXTranslationUnit TU;
2072 struct CXUnsavedFile *unsaved_files = 0;
2073 int num_unsaved_files = 0;
2074 int compiler_arg_idx = 0;
2075 enum CXErrorCode Err;
2076 int result, i;
2077 int trial;
2078 int remap_after_trial = 0;
2079 char *endptr = 0;
2080
2081 Idx = clang_createIndex(/* excludeDeclsFromPCH */
2082 !strcmp(filter, "local") ? 1 : 0,
2083 /* displayDiagnostics=*/1);
2084
2085 if (parse_remapped_files(argc, argv, 0, &unsaved_files, &num_unsaved_files)) {
2086 clang_disposeIndex(Idx);
2087 return -1;
2088 }
2089
2090 for (i = 0; i < argc; ++i) {
2091 if (strcmp(argv[i], "--") == 0)
2092 break;
2093 }
2094 if (i < argc)
2095 compiler_arg_idx = i+1;
2096 if (num_unsaved_files > compiler_arg_idx)
2097 compiler_arg_idx = num_unsaved_files;
2098
2099 /* Load the initial translation unit -- we do this without honoring remapped
2100 * files, so that we have a way to test results after changing the source. */
2101 Err = clang_parseTranslationUnit2(Idx, 0,
2102 argv + compiler_arg_idx,
2103 argc - compiler_arg_idx,
2104 0, 0, getDefaultParsingOptions(), &TU);
2105 if (Err != CXError_Success) {
2106 fprintf(stderr, "Unable to load translation unit!\n");
2107 describeLibclangFailure(Err);
2108 free_remapped_files(unsaved_files, num_unsaved_files);
2109 clang_disposeIndex(Idx);
2110 return 1;
2111 }
2112
2113 if (checkForErrors(TU) != 0)
2114 return -1;
2115
2116 if (getenv("CINDEXTEST_REMAP_AFTER_TRIAL")) {
2117 remap_after_trial =
2118 strtol(getenv("CINDEXTEST_REMAP_AFTER_TRIAL"), &endptr, 10);
2119 }
2120
2121 for (trial = 0; trial < trials; ++trial) {
2122 free_remapped_files(unsaved_files, num_unsaved_files);
2123 if (parse_remapped_files_with_try(trial, argc, argv, 0,
2124 &unsaved_files, &num_unsaved_files)) {
2125 clang_disposeTranslationUnit(TU);
2126 clang_disposeIndex(Idx);
2127 return -1;
2128 }
2129
2130 Err = clang_reparseTranslationUnit(
2131 TU,
2132 trial >= remap_after_trial ? num_unsaved_files : 0,
2133 trial >= remap_after_trial ? unsaved_files : 0,
2134 clang_defaultReparseOptions(TU));
2135 if (Err != CXError_Success) {
2136 fprintf(stderr, "Unable to reparse translation unit!\n");
2137 describeLibclangFailure(Err);
2138 clang_disposeTranslationUnit(TU);
2139 free_remapped_files(unsaved_files, num_unsaved_files);
2140 clang_disposeIndex(Idx);
2141 return -1;
2142 }
2143
2144 if (checkForErrors(TU) != 0)
2145 return -1;
2146 }
2147
2148 result = perform_test_load(Idx, TU, filter, NULL, Visitor, PV, NULL);
2149
2150 free_remapped_files(unsaved_files, num_unsaved_files);
2151 clang_disposeIndex(Idx);
2152 return result;
2153}

2200static int perform_file_scan(const char *ast_file, const char *source_file,
2201 const char *prefix) {
2202 CXIndex Idx;
2203 CXTranslationUnit TU;
2204 FILE *fp;
2205 CXCursor prevCursor = clang_getNullCursor();
2206 CXFile file;
2207 unsigned line = 1, col = 1;
2208 unsigned start_line = 1, start_col = 1;
2209
2210 if (!(Idx = clang_createIndex(/* excludeDeclsFromPCH */ 1,
2211 /* displayDiagnostics=*/1))) {
2212 fprintf(stderr, "Could not create Index\n");
2213 return 1;
2214 }
2215
2216 if (!CreateTranslationUnit(Idx, ast_file, &TU))
2217 return 1;
2218
2219 if ((fp = fopen(source_file, "r")) == NULL) {
2220 fprintf(stderr, "Could not open '%s'\n", source_file);
2221 clang_disposeTranslationUnit(TU);
2222 return 1;
2223 }
2224
2225 file = clang_getFile(TU, source_file);
2226 for (;;) {
2227 CXCursor cursor;
2228 int c = fgetc(fp);
2229
2230 if (c == '\n') {
2231 ++line;
2232 col = 1;
2233 } else
2234 ++col;
2235
2236 /* Check the cursor at this position, and dump the previous one if we have
2237 * found something new.
2238 */
2239 cursor = clang_getCursor(TU, clang_getLocation(TU, file, line, col));
2240 if ((c == EOF || !clang_equalCursors(cursor, prevCursor)) &&
2241 prevCursor.kind != CXCursor_InvalidFile) {
2242 print_cursor_file_scan(TU, prevCursor, start_line, start_col,
2243 line, col, prefix);
2244 start_line = line;
2245 start_col = col;
2246 }
2247 if (c == EOF)
2248 break;
2249
2250 prevCursor = cursor;
2251 }
2252
2253 fclose(fp);
2254 clang_disposeTranslationUnit(TU);
2255 clang_disposeIndex(Idx);
2256 return 0;
2257}

2259/******************************************************************************/
2260/* Logic for testing clang code completion. */
2261/******************************************************************************/
2262
2263/* Parse file:line:column from the input string. Returns 0 on success, non-zero
2264 on failure. If successful, the pointer *filename will contain newly-allocated
2265 memory (that will be owned by the caller) to store the file name. */
2266int parse_file_line_column(const char *input, char **filename, unsigned *line,
2267 unsigned *column, unsigned *second_line,
2268 unsigned *second_column) {
2269 /* Find the second colon. */
2270 const char *last_colon = strrchr(input, ':');
2271 unsigned values[4], i;
2272 unsigned num_values = (second_line && second_column)? 4 : 2;
2273
2274 char *endptr = 0;
2275 if (!last_colon || last_colon == input) {
2276 if (num_values == 4)
2277 fprintf(stderr, "could not parse filename:line:column:line:column in "
2278 "'%s'\n", input);
2279 else
2280 fprintf(stderr, "could not parse filename:line:column in '%s'\n", input);
2281 return 1;
2282 }
2283
2284 for (i = 0; i != num_values; ++i) {
2285 const char *prev_colon;
2286
2287 /* Parse the next line or column. */
2288 values[num_values - i - 1] = strtol(last_colon + 1, &endptr, 10);
2289 if (*endptr != 0 && *endptr != ':') {
2290 fprintf(stderr, "could not parse %s in '%s'\n",
2291 (i % 2 ? "column" : "line"), input);
2292 return 1;
2293 }
2294
2295 if (i + 1 == num_values)
2296 break;
2297
2298 /* Find the previous colon. */
2299 prev_colon = last_colon - 1;
2300 while (prev_colon != input && *prev_colon != ':')
2301 --prev_colon;
2302 if (prev_colon == input) {
2303 fprintf(stderr, "could not parse %s in '%s'\n",
2304 (i % 2 == 0? "column" : "line"), input);
2305 return 1;
2306 }
2307
2308 last_colon = prev_colon;
2309 }
2310
2311 *line = values[0];
2312 *column = values[1];
2313
2314 if (second_line && second_column) {
2315 *second_line = values[2];
2316 *second_column = values[3];
2317 }
2318
2319 /* Copy the file name. */
2320 *filename = (char*)malloc(last_colon - input + 1);
2321 assert(*filename);
2322 memcpy(*filename, input, last_colon - input);
2323 (*filename)[last_colon - input] = 0;
2324 return 0;
2325}

2356static int checkForErrors(CXTranslationUnit TU) {
2357 unsigned Num, i;
2358 CXDiagnostic Diag;
2359 CXString DiagStr;
2360
2361 if (!getenv("CINDEXTEST_FAILONERROR"))
2362 return 0;
2363
2364 Num = clang_getNumDiagnostics(TU);
2365 for (i = 0; i != Num; ++i) {
2366 Diag = clang_getDiagnostic(TU, i);
2367 if (clang_getDiagnosticSeverity(Diag) >= CXDiagnostic_Error) {
2368 DiagStr = clang_formatDiagnostic(Diag,
2369 clang_defaultDiagnosticDisplayOptions());
2370 fprintf(stderr, "%s\n", clang_getCString(DiagStr));
2371 clang_disposeString(DiagStr);
2372 clang_disposeDiagnostic(Diag);
2373 return -1;
2374 }
2375 clang_disposeDiagnostic(Diag);
2376 }
2377
2378 return 0;

2409 clang_getCompletionChunkKindSpelling(Kind),

2438static void print_completion_result(CXTranslationUnit translation_unit,
2439 CXCodeCompleteResults *completion_results,
2440 unsigned index,
2441 FILE *file) {

2443 CXString ks = clang_getCursorKindSpelling(completion_result->CursorKind);

2462 case CXAvailability_Deprecated:
2463 fprintf(file, " (deprecated)");
2464 break;
2465
2466 case CXAvailability_NotAvailable:
2467 fprintf(file, " (unavailable)");

2497 clang_getCString(KindSpelling),
2498 clang_getCString(ParentName));
2499 clang_disposeString(KindSpelling);
2500 }
2501 clang_disposeString(ParentName);

2503
2504 BriefComment = clang_getCompletionBriefComment(
2505 completion_result->CompletionString);

2512 for (i = 0; i < clang_getCompletionNumFixIts(completion_results, index);
2513 ++i) {

2516 &correction_range);
2517 fprintf(file, " (requires fix-it: ");

2520 fprintf(file, " to \"%s\")", clang_getCString(FixIt));

2600int perform_code_completion(int argc, const char **argv, int timing_only) {
2601 const char *input = argv[1];
2602 char *filename = 0;
2603 unsigned line;
2604 unsigned column;
2605 CXIndex CIdx;
2606 int errorCode;
2607 struct CXUnsavedFile *unsaved_files = 0;
2608 int num_unsaved_files = 0;
2609 CXCodeCompleteResults *results = 0;
2610 enum CXErrorCode Err;
2611 CXTranslationUnit TU;
2612 unsigned I, Repeats = 1;
2613 unsigned completionOptions = clang_defaultCodeCompleteOptions();
2614 const char *InvocationPath;
2615
2616 if (getenv("CINDEXTEST_CODE_COMPLETE_PATTERNS"))
2617 completionOptions |= CXCodeComplete_IncludeCodePatterns;
2618 if (getenv("CINDEXTEST_COMPLETION_BRIEF_COMMENTS"))
2619 completionOptions |= CXCodeComplete_IncludeBriefComments;
2620 if (getenv("CINDEXTEST_COMPLETION_SKIP_PREAMBLE"))
2621 completionOptions |= CXCodeComplete_SkipPreamble;
2622 if (getenv("CINDEXTEST_COMPLETION_INCLUDE_FIXITS"))
2623 completionOptions |= CXCodeComplete_IncludeCompletionsWithFixIts;
2624
2625 if (timing_only)
2626 input += strlen("-code-completion-timing=");
2627 else
2628 input += strlen("-code-completion-at=");
2629
2630 if ((errorCode = parse_file_line_column(input, &filename, &line, &column,
2631 0, 0)))
2632 return errorCode;
2633
2634 if (parse_remapped_files(argc, argv, 2, &unsaved_files, &num_unsaved_files))
2635 return -1;
2636
2637 CIdx = clang_createIndex(0, 0);
2638 InvocationPath = getenv("CINDEXTEST_INVOCATION_EMISSION_PATH");
2639 if (InvocationPath)
2640 clang_CXIndex_setInvocationEmissionPathOption(CIdx, InvocationPath);
2641
2642 if (getenv("CINDEXTEST_EDITING"))
2643 Repeats = 5;
2644
2645 Err = clang_parseTranslationUnit2(CIdx, 0,
2646 argv + num_unsaved_files + 2,
2647 argc - num_unsaved_files - 2,
2648 0, 0, getDefaultParsingOptions(), &TU);
2649 if (Err != CXError_Success) {
2650 fprintf(stderr, "Unable to load translation unit!\n");
2651 describeLibclangFailure(Err);
2652 return 1;
2653 }
2654
2655 Err = clang_reparseTranslationUnit(TU, 0, 0,
2656 clang_defaultReparseOptions(TU));
2657
2658 if (Err != CXError_Success) {
2659 fprintf(stderr, "Unable to reparse translation unit!\n");
2660 describeLibclangFailure(Err);
2661 clang_disposeTranslationUnit(TU);
2662 return 1;
2663 }
2664
2665 for (I = 0; I != Repeats; ++I) {
2666 results = clang_codeCompleteAt(TU, filename, line, column,
2667 unsaved_files, num_unsaved_files,
2668 completionOptions);
2669 if (!results) {
2670 fprintf(stderr, "Unable to perform code completion!\n");
2671 return 1;
2672 }
2673 if (I != Repeats-1)
2674 clang_disposeCodeCompleteResults(results);
2675 }
2676
2677 if (results) {
2678 unsigned i, n = results->NumResults, containerIsIncomplete = 0;
2679 unsigned long long contexts;
2680 enum CXCursorKind containerKind;
2681 CXString objCSelector;
2682 const char *selectorString;
2683 if (!timing_only) {
2684 /* Sort the code-completion results based on the typed text. */
2685 clang_sortCodeCompletionResults(results->Results, results->NumResults);
2686
2687 for (i = 0; i != n; ++i)
2688 print_completion_result(TU, results, i, stdout);
2689 }
2690 n = clang_codeCompleteGetNumDiagnostics(results);
2691 for (i = 0; i != n; ++i) {
2692 CXDiagnostic diag = clang_codeCompleteGetDiagnostic(results, i);
2693 PrintDiagnostic(diag);
2694 clang_disposeDiagnostic(diag);
2695 }
2696
2697 contexts = clang_codeCompleteGetContexts(results);
2698 print_completion_contexts(contexts, stdout);
2699
2700 containerKind = clang_codeCompleteGetContainerKind(results,
2701 &containerIsIncomplete);
2702
2703 if (containerKind != CXCursor_InvalidCode) {
2704 /* We have found a container */
2705 CXString containerUSR, containerKindSpelling;
2706 containerKindSpelling = clang_getCursorKindSpelling(containerKind);
2707 printf("Container Kind: %s\n", clang_getCString(containerKindSpelling));
2708 clang_disposeString(containerKindSpelling);
2709
2710 if (containerIsIncomplete) {
2711 printf("Container is incomplete\n");
2712 }
2713 else {
2714 printf("Container is complete\n");
2715 }
2716
2717 containerUSR = clang_codeCompleteGetContainerUSR(results);
2718 printf("Container USR: %s\n", clang_getCString(containerUSR));
2719 clang_disposeString(containerUSR);
2720 }
2721
2722 objCSelector = clang_codeCompleteGetObjCSelector(results);
2723 selectorString = clang_getCString(objCSelector);
2724 if (selectorString && strlen(selectorString) > 0) {
2725 printf("Objective-C selector: %s\n", selectorString);
2726 }
2727 clang_disposeString(objCSelector);
2728
2729 clang_disposeCodeCompleteResults(results);
2730 }
2731 clang_disposeTranslationUnit(TU);
2732 clang_disposeIndex(CIdx);
2733 free(filename);
2734
2735 free_remapped_files(unsaved_files, num_unsaved_files);
2736
2737 return 0;
2738}

2748static int inspect_cursor_at(int argc, const char **argv,
2749 const char *locations_flag,
2750 cursor_handler_t handler) {
2751 CXIndex CIdx;
2752 int errorCode;
2753 struct CXUnsavedFile *unsaved_files = 0;
2754 int num_unsaved_files = 0;
2755 enum CXErrorCode Err;
2756 CXTranslationUnit TU;
2757 CXCursor Cursor;
2758 CursorSourceLocation *Locations = 0;
2759 unsigned NumLocations = 0, Loc;
2760 unsigned Repeats = 1;
2761 unsigned I;
2762
2763 /* Count the number of locations. */
2764 while (strstr(argv[NumLocations+1], locations_flag) == argv[NumLocations+1])
2765 ++NumLocations;
2766
2767 /* Parse the locations. */
2768 assert(NumLocations > 0 && "Unable to count locations?");
2769 Locations = (CursorSourceLocation *)malloc(
2770 NumLocations * sizeof(CursorSourceLocation));
2771 assert(Locations);
2772 for (Loc = 0; Loc < NumLocations; ++Loc) {
2773 const char *input = argv[Loc + 1] + strlen(locations_flag);
2774 if ((errorCode = parse_file_line_column(input, &Locations[Loc].filename,
2775 &Locations[Loc].line,
2776 &Locations[Loc].column, 0, 0)))
2777 return errorCode;
2778 }
2779
2780 if (parse_remapped_files(argc, argv, NumLocations + 1, &unsaved_files,
2781 &num_unsaved_files))
2782 return -1;
2783
2784 if (getenv("CINDEXTEST_EDITING"))
2785 Repeats = 5;
2786
2787 /* Parse the translation unit. When we're testing clang_getCursor() after
2788 reparsing, don't remap unsaved files until the second parse. */
2789 CIdx = clang_createIndex(1, 1);
2790 Err = clang_parseTranslationUnit2(CIdx, argv[argc - 1],
2791 argv + num_unsaved_files + 1 + NumLocations,
2792 argc - num_unsaved_files - 2 - NumLocations,
2793 unsaved_files,
2794 Repeats > 1? 0 : num_unsaved_files,
2795 getDefaultParsingOptions(), &TU);
2796 if (Err != CXError_Success) {
2797 fprintf(stderr, "unable to parse input\n");
2798 describeLibclangFailure(Err);
2799 return -1;
2800 }
2801
2802 if (checkForErrors(TU) != 0)
2803 return -1;
2804
2805 for (I = 0; I != Repeats; ++I) {
2806 if (Repeats > 1) {
2807 Err = clang_reparseTranslationUnit(TU, num_unsaved_files, unsaved_files,
2808 clang_defaultReparseOptions(TU));
2809 if (Err != CXError_Success) {
2810 describeLibclangFailure(Err);
2811 clang_disposeTranslationUnit(TU);
2812 return 1;
2813 }
2814 }
2815
2816 if (checkForErrors(TU) != 0)
2817 return -1;
2818
2819 for (Loc = 0; Loc < NumLocations; ++Loc) {
2820 CXFile file = clang_getFile(TU, Locations[Loc].filename);
2821 if (!file)
2822 continue;
2823
2824 Cursor = clang_getCursor(TU,
2825 clang_getLocation(TU, file, Locations[Loc].line,
2826 Locations[Loc].column));
2827
2828 if (checkForErrors(TU) != 0)
2829 return -1;
2830
2831 if (I + 1 == Repeats) {
2832 handler(Cursor);
2833 free(Locations[Loc].filename);
2834 }
2835 }
2836 }
2837
2838 PrintDiagnostics(TU);
2839 clang_disposeTranslationUnit(TU);
2840 clang_disposeIndex(CIdx);
2841 free(Locations);
2842 free_remapped_files(unsaved_files, num_unsaved_files);
2843 return 0;
2844}

2846static void inspect_print_cursor(CXCursor Cursor) {
2847 CXTranslationUnit TU = clang_Cursor_getTranslationUnit(Cursor);
2848 CXCompletionString completionString = clang_getCursorCompletionString(
2849 Cursor);
2850 CXSourceLocation CursorLoc = clang_getCursorLocation(Cursor);
2851 CXString Spelling;
2852 const char *cspell;
2853 unsigned line, column;
2854 clang_getSpellingLocation(CursorLoc, 0, &line, &column, 0);
2855 printf("%d:%d ", line, column);
2856 PrintCursor(Cursor, NULL);
2857 PrintCursorExtent(Cursor);
2858 Spelling = clang_getCursorSpelling(Cursor);
2859 cspell = clang_getCString(Spelling);
2860 if (cspell && strlen(cspell) != 0) {
2861 unsigned pieceIndex;
2862 printf(" Spelling=%s (", cspell);
2863 for (pieceIndex = 0; ; ++pieceIndex) {
2864 CXSourceRange range =
2865 clang_Cursor_getSpellingNameRange(Cursor, pieceIndex, 0);
2866 if (clang_Range_isNull(range))
2867 break;
2868 PrintRange(range, 0);
2869 }
2870 printf(")");
2871 }
2872 clang_disposeString(Spelling);
2873 if (clang_Cursor_getObjCSelectorIndex(Cursor) != -1)
2874 printf(" Selector index=%d",
2875 clang_Cursor_getObjCSelectorIndex(Cursor));
2876 if (clang_Cursor_isDynamicCall(Cursor))
2877 printf(" Dynamic-call");
2878 if (Cursor.kind == CXCursor_ObjCMessageExpr ||
2879 Cursor.kind == CXCursor_MemberRefExpr) {
2880 CXType T = clang_Cursor_getReceiverType(Cursor);
2881 if (T.kind != CXType_Invalid) {
2882 CXString S = clang_getTypeKindSpelling(T.kind);
2883 printf(" Receiver-type=%s", clang_getCString(S));
2884 clang_disposeString(S);
2885 }
2886 }
2887
2888 {
2889 CXModule mod = clang_Cursor_getModule(Cursor);
2890 CXFile astFile;
2891 CXString name, astFilename;
2892 unsigned i, numHeaders;
2893 if (mod) {
2894 astFile = clang_Module_getASTFile(mod);
2895 astFilename = clang_getFileName(astFile);
2896 name = clang_Module_getFullName(mod);
2897 numHeaders = clang_Module_getNumTopLevelHeaders(TU, mod);
2898 printf(" ModuleName=%s (%s) system=%d Headers(%d):",
2899 clang_getCString(name), clang_getCString(astFilename),
2900 clang_Module_isSystem(mod), numHeaders);
2901 clang_disposeString(name);
2902 clang_disposeString(astFilename);
2903 for (i = 0; i < numHeaders; ++i) {
2904 CXFile file = clang_Module_getTopLevelHeader(TU, mod, i);
2905 CXString filename = clang_getFileName(file);
2906 printf("\n%s", clang_getCString(filename));
2907 clang_disposeString(filename);
2908 }
2909 }
2910 }
2911
2912 if (completionString != NULL) {
2913 printf("\nCompletion string: ");
2914 print_completion_string(completionString, stdout);
2915 }
2916 printf("\n");
2917}

2919static void display_evaluate_results(CXEvalResult result) {
2920 switch (clang_EvalResult_getKind(result)) {
2921 case CXEval_Int:
2922 {
2923 printf("Kind: Int, ");
2924 if (clang_EvalResult_isUnsignedInt(result)) {
2925 unsigned long long val = clang_EvalResult_getAsUnsigned(result);
2926 printf("unsigned, Value: %llu", val);
2927 } else {
2928 long long val = clang_EvalResult_getAsLongLong(result);
2929 printf("Value: %lld", val);
2930 }
2931 break;
2932 }
2933 case CXEval_Float:
2934 {
2935 double val = clang_EvalResult_getAsDouble(result);
2936 printf("Kind: Float , Value: %f", val);
2937 break;
2938 }
2939 case CXEval_ObjCStrLiteral:
2940 {
2941 const char* str = clang_EvalResult_getAsStr(result);
2942 printf("Kind: ObjCString , Value: %s", str);
2943 break;
2944 }
2945 case CXEval_StrLiteral:
2946 {
2947 const char* str = clang_EvalResult_getAsStr(result);
2948 printf("Kind: CString , Value: %s", str);
2949 break;
2950 }
2951 case CXEval_CFStr:
2952 {
2953 const char* str = clang_EvalResult_getAsStr(result);
2954 printf("Kind: CFString , Value: %s", str);
2955 break;
2956 }
2957 default:
2958 printf("Unexposed");
2959 break;
2960 }
2961}

3393 newStr = node->data;
3394 sprintf(newStr, "%s:%d:%d", name, line, column);
3395
3396 /* Remember string so it can be freed later. */
3397 index_data = (IndexData *)client_data;
3398 node->next = index_data->strings;
3399 index_data->strings = node;
3400
3401 return (CXIdxClientContainer)newStr;
3402}
