3654static void index_indexDeclaration(CXClientData client_data,
3655 const CXIdxDeclInfo *info) {
3656 IndexData *index_data;
3657 const CXIdxObjCCategoryDeclInfo *CatInfo;
3658 const CXIdxObjCInterfaceDeclInfo *InterInfo;
3659 const CXIdxObjCProtocolRefListInfo *ProtoInfo;
3660 const CXIdxObjCPropertyDeclInfo *PropInfo;
3661 const CXIdxCXXClassDeclInfo *CXXClassInfo;
3662 unsigned i;
3663 index_data = (IndexData *)client_data;
3664
3665 printEntityInfo("[indexDeclaration]", client_data, info->entityInfo);
3666 printf(" | cursor: ");
3667 PrintCursor(info->cursor, NULL);
3668 printf(" | loc: ");
3669 printCXIndexLoc(info->loc, client_data);
3670 printf(" | semantic-container: ");
3671 printCXIndexContainer(info->semanticContainer);
3672 printf(" | lexical-container: ");
3673 printCXIndexContainer(info->lexicalContainer);
3674 printf(" | isRedecl: %d", info->isRedeclaration);
3675 printf(" | isDef: %d", info->isDefinition);
3676 if (info->flags & CXIdxDeclFlag_Skipped) {
3677 assert(!info->isContainer);
3678 printf(" | isContainer: skipped");
3679 } else {
3680 printf(" | isContainer: %d", info->isContainer);
3681 }
3682 printf(" | isImplicit: %d\n", info->isImplicit);
3683
3684 for (i = 0; i != info->numAttributes; ++i) {
3685 const CXIdxAttrInfo *Attr = info->attributes[i];
3686 printf(" <attribute>: ");
3687 PrintCursor(Attr->cursor, NULL);
3688 printf("\n");
3689 }
3690
3691 if (clang_index_isEntityObjCContainerKind(info->entityInfo->kind)) {
3692 const char *kindName = 0;
3693 CXIdxObjCContainerKind K = clang_index_getObjCContainerDeclInfo(info)->kind;
3694 switch (K) {
3695 case CXIdxObjCContainer_ForwardRef:
3696 kindName = "forward-ref"; break;
3697 case CXIdxObjCContainer_Interface:
3698 kindName = "interface"; break;
3699 case CXIdxObjCContainer_Implementation:
3700 kindName = "implementation"; break;
3701 }
3702 printCheck(index_data);
3703 printf(" <ObjCContainerInfo>: kind: %s\n", kindName);
3704 }
3705
3706 if ((CatInfo = clang_index_getObjCCategoryDeclInfo(info))) {
3707 printEntityInfo(" <ObjCCategoryInfo>: class", client_data,
3708 CatInfo->objcClass);
3709 printf(" | cursor: ");
3710 PrintCursor(CatInfo->classCursor, NULL);
3711 printf(" | loc: ");
3712 printCXIndexLoc(CatInfo->classLoc, client_data);
3713 printf("\n");
3714 }
3715
3716 if ((InterInfo = clang_index_getObjCInterfaceDeclInfo(info))) {
3717 if (InterInfo->superInfo) {
3718 printBaseClassInfo(client_data, InterInfo->superInfo);
3719 printf("\n");
3720 }
3721 }
3722
3723 if ((ProtoInfo = clang_index_getObjCProtocolRefListInfo(info))) {
3724 printProtocolList(ProtoInfo, client_data);
3725 }
3726
3727 if ((PropInfo = clang_index_getObjCPropertyDeclInfo(info))) {
3728 if (PropInfo->getter) {
3729 printEntityInfo(" <getter>", client_data, PropInfo->getter);
3730 printf("\n");
3731 }
3732 if (PropInfo->setter) {
3733 printEntityInfo(" <setter>", client_data, PropInfo->setter);
3734 printf("\n");
3735 }
3736 }
3737
3738 if ((CXXClassInfo = clang_index_getCXXClassDeclInfo(info))) {
3739 for (i = 0; i != CXXClassInfo->numBases; ++i) {
3740 printBaseClassInfo(client_data, CXXClassInfo->bases[i]);
3741 printf("\n");
3742 }
3743 }
3744
3745 if (info->declAsContainer)
3746 clang_index_setClientContainer(
3747 info->declAsContainer,
3748 makeClientContainer(client_data, info->entityInfo, info->loc));
3749}

3789static unsigned getIndexOptions(void) {
3790 unsigned index_opts;
3791 index_opts = 0;
3792 if (getenv("CINDEXTEST_SUPPRESSREFS"))
3793 index_opts |= CXIndexOpt_SuppressRedundantRefs;
3794 if (getenv("CINDEXTEST_INDEXLOCALSYMBOLS"))
3795 index_opts |= CXIndexOpt_IndexFunctionLocalSymbols;
3796 if (!getenv("CINDEXTEST_DISABLE_SKIPPARSEDBODIES"))
3797 index_opts |= CXIndexOpt_SkipParsedBodiesInSession;
3798 if (getenv("CINDEXTEST_INDEXIMPLICITTEMPLATEINSTANTIATIONS"))
3799 index_opts |= CXIndexOpt_IndexImplicitTemplateInstantiations;
3800

3804static int index_compile_args(int num_args, const char **args,
3805 CXIndexAction idxAction,
3806 ImportedASTFilesData *importedASTs,
3807 const char *check_prefix) {
3808 IndexData index_data;
3809 unsigned index_opts;
3810 int result;
3811
3812 if (num_args == 0) {
3813 fprintf(stderr, "no compiler arguments\n");
3814 return -1;
3815 }
3816
3817 index_data.check_prefix = check_prefix;
3818 index_data.first_check_printed = 0;
3819 index_data.fail_for_error = 0;
3820 index_data.abort = 0;
3821 index_data.main_filename = createCXString("");
3822 index_data.importedASTs = importedASTs;
3823 index_data.strings = NULL;
3824 index_data.TU = NULL;
3825
3826 index_opts = getIndexOptions();
3827 result = clang_indexSourceFile(idxAction, &index_data,
3828 &IndexCB,sizeof(IndexCB), index_opts,
3829 0, args, num_args, 0, 0, 0,
3830 getDefaultParsingOptions());
3831 if (result != CXError_Success)
3832 describeLibclangFailure(result);
3833
3834 if (index_data.fail_for_error)
3835 result = -1;
3836
3837 clang_disposeString(index_data.main_filename);
3838 free_client_data(&index_data);
3839 return result;
3840}

3877static int index_file(int argc, const char **argv, int full) {
3878 const char *check_prefix;
3879 CXIndex Idx;
3880 CXIndexAction idxAction;
3881 ImportedASTFilesData *importedASTs;
3882 int result;
3883
3884 check_prefix = 0;
3885 if (argc > 0) {
3886 if (strstr(argv[0], "-check-prefix=") == argv[0]) {
3887 check_prefix = argv[0] + strlen("-check-prefix=");
3888 ++argv;
3889 --argc;
3890 }
3891 }
3892
3893 if (!(Idx = clang_createIndex(/* excludeDeclsFromPCH */ 1,
3894 /* displayDiagnostics=*/1))) {
3895 fprintf(stderr, "Could not create Index\n");
3896 return 1;
3897 }
3898 idxAction = clang_IndexAction_create(Idx);
3899 importedASTs = 0;
3900 if (full)
3901 importedASTs = importedASTs_create();
3902
3903 result = index_compile_args(argc, argv, idxAction, importedASTs, check_prefix);
3904 if (result != 0)
3905 goto finished;
3906
3907 if (full) {
3908 unsigned i;
3909 for (i = 0; i < importedASTs->num_files && result == 0; ++i) {
3910 result = index_ast_file(importedASTs->filenames[i], Idx, idxAction,
3911 importedASTs, check_prefix);
3912 }
3913 }
3914
3915finished:
3916 importedASTs_dispose(importedASTs);
3917 clang_IndexAction_dispose(idxAction);
3918 clang_disposeIndex(Idx);
3919 return result;
3920}

3952static int index_compile_db(int argc, const char **argv) {
3953 const char *check_prefix;
3954 CXIndex Idx;
3955 CXIndexAction idxAction;
3956 int errorCode = 0;
3957
3958 check_prefix = 0;
3959 if (argc > 0) {
3960 if (strstr(argv[0], "-check-prefix=") == argv[0]) {
3961 check_prefix = argv[0] + strlen("-check-prefix=");
3962 ++argv;
3963 --argc;
3964 }
3965 }
3966
3967 if (argc == 0) {
3968 fprintf(stderr, "no compilation database\n");
3969 return -1;
3970 }
3971
3972 if (!(Idx = clang_createIndex(/* excludeDeclsFromPCH */ 1,
3973 /* displayDiagnostics=*/1))) {
3974 fprintf(stderr, "Could not create Index\n");
3975 return 1;
3976 }
3977 idxAction = clang_IndexAction_create(Idx);
3978
3979 {
3980 const char *database = argv[0];
3981 CXCompilationDatabase db = 0;
3982 CXCompileCommands CCmds = 0;
3983 CXCompileCommand CCmd;
3984 CXCompilationDatabase_Error ec;
3985 CXString wd;
3986#define MAX_COMPILE_ARGS 512
3987 CXString cxargs[MAX_COMPILE_ARGS];
3988 const char *args[MAX_COMPILE_ARGS];
3989 char *tmp;
3990 unsigned len;
3991 char *buildDir;
3992 int i, a, numCmds, numArgs;
3993
3994 len = strlen(database);
3995 tmp = (char *) malloc(len+1);
3996 assert(tmp);
3997 memcpy(tmp, database, len+1);
3998 buildDir = dirname(tmp);
3999
4000 db = clang_CompilationDatabase_fromDirectory(buildDir, &ec);
4001
4002 if (db) {
4003
4004 if (ec!=CXCompilationDatabase_NoError) {
4005 printf("unexpected error %d code while loading compilation database\n", ec);
4006 errorCode = -1;
4007 goto cdb_end;
4008 }
4009
4010 if (chdir(buildDir) != 0) {
4011 printf("Could not chdir to %s\n", buildDir);
4012 errorCode = -1;
4013 goto cdb_end;
4014 }
4015
4016 CCmds = clang_CompilationDatabase_getAllCompileCommands(db);
4017 if (!CCmds) {
4018 printf("compilation db is empty\n");
4019 errorCode = -1;
4020 goto cdb_end;
4021 }
4022
4023 numCmds = clang_CompileCommands_getSize(CCmds);
4024
4025 if (numCmds==0) {
4026 fprintf(stderr, "should not get an empty compileCommand set\n");
4027 errorCode = -1;
4028 goto cdb_end;
4029 }
4030
4031 for (i=0; i<numCmds && errorCode == 0; ++i) {
4032 CCmd = clang_CompileCommands_getCommand(CCmds, i);
4033
4034 wd = clang_CompileCommand_getDirectory(CCmd);
4035 if (chdir(clang_getCString(wd)) != 0) {
4036 printf("Could not chdir to %s\n", clang_getCString(wd));
4037 errorCode = -1;
4038 goto cdb_end;
4039 }
4040 clang_disposeString(wd);
4041
4042 numArgs = clang_CompileCommand_getNumArgs(CCmd);
4043 if (numArgs > MAX_COMPILE_ARGS){
4044 fprintf(stderr, "got more compile arguments than maximum\n");
4045 errorCode = -1;
4046 goto cdb_end;
4047 }
4048 for (a=0; a<numArgs; ++a) {
4049 cxargs[a] = clang_CompileCommand_getArg(CCmd, a);
4050 args[a] = clang_getCString(cxargs[a]);
4051 }
4052
4053 errorCode = index_compile_args(numArgs, args, idxAction,
4054 /*importedASTs=*/0, check_prefix);
4055
4056 for (a=0; a<numArgs; ++a)
4057 clang_disposeString(cxargs[a]);
4058 }
4059 } else {
4060 printf("database loading failed with error code %d.\n", ec);
4061 errorCode = -1;
4062 }
4063
4064 cdb_end:
4065 clang_CompileCommands_dispose(CCmds);
4066 clang_CompilationDatabase_dispose(db);
4067 free(tmp);
4068
4069 }
4070
4071 clang_IndexAction_dispose(idxAction);
4072 clang_disposeIndex(Idx);
4073 return errorCode;
4074}
4075
4076int perform_token_annotation(int argc, const char **argv) {
4077 const char *input = argv[1];
4078 char *filename = 0;
4079 unsigned line, second_line;
4080 unsigned column, second_column;
4081 CXIndex CIdx;
4082 CXTranslationUnit TU = 0;
4083 int errorCode;
4084 struct CXUnsavedFile *unsaved_files = 0;
4085 int num_unsaved_files = 0;
4086 CXToken *tokens;
4087 unsigned num_tokens;
4088 CXSourceRange range;
4089 CXSourceLocation startLoc, endLoc;
4090 CXFile file = 0;
4091 CXCursor *cursors = 0;
4092 CXSourceRangeList *skipped_ranges = 0;
4093 enum CXErrorCode Err;
4094 unsigned i;
4095
4096 input += strlen("-test-annotate-tokens=");
4097 if ((errorCode = parse_file_line_column(input, &filename, &line, &column,
4098 &second_line, &second_column)))
4099 return errorCode;
4100
4101 if (parse_remapped_files(argc, argv, 2, &unsaved_files, &num_unsaved_files)) {
4102 free(filename);
4103 return -1;
4104 }
4105
4106 CIdx = clang_createIndex(0, 1);
4107 Err = clang_parseTranslationUnit2(CIdx, argv[argc - 1],
4108 argv + num_unsaved_files + 2,
4109 argc - num_unsaved_files - 3,
4110 unsaved_files,
4111 num_unsaved_files,
4112 getDefaultParsingOptions(), &TU);
4113 if (Err != CXError_Success) {
4114 fprintf(stderr, "unable to parse input\n");
4115 describeLibclangFailure(Err);
4116 clang_disposeIndex(CIdx);
4117 free(filename);
4118 free_remapped_files(unsaved_files, num_unsaved_files);
4119 return -1;
4120 }
4121 errorCode = 0;
4122
4123 if (checkForErrors(TU) != 0) {
4124 errorCode = -1;
4125 goto teardown;
4126 }
4127
4128 if (getenv("CINDEXTEST_EDITING")) {
4129 for (i = 0; i < 5; ++i) {
4130 Err = clang_reparseTranslationUnit(TU, num_unsaved_files, unsaved_files,
4131 clang_defaultReparseOptions(TU));
4132 if (Err != CXError_Success) {
4133 fprintf(stderr, "Unable to reparse translation unit!\n");
4134 describeLibclangFailure(Err);
4135 errorCode = -1;
4136 goto teardown;
4137 }
4138 }
4139 }
4140
4141 if (checkForErrors(TU) != 0) {
4142 errorCode = -1;
4143 goto teardown;
4144 }
4145
4146 file = clang_getFile(TU, filename);
4147 if (!file) {
4148 fprintf(stderr, "file %s is not in this translation unit\n", filename);
4149 errorCode = -1;
4150 goto teardown;
4151 }
4152
4153 startLoc = clang_getLocation(TU, file, line, column);
4154 if (clang_equalLocations(clang_getNullLocation(), startLoc)) {
4155 fprintf(stderr, "invalid source location %s:%d:%d\n", filename, line,
4156 column);
4157 errorCode = -1;
4158 goto teardown;
4159 }
4160
4161 endLoc = clang_getLocation(TU, file, second_line, second_column);
4162 if (clang_equalLocations(clang_getNullLocation(), endLoc)) {
4163 fprintf(stderr, "invalid source location %s:%d:%d\n", filename,
4164 second_line, second_column);
4165 errorCode = -1;
4166 goto teardown;
4167 }
4168
4169 range = clang_getRange(startLoc, endLoc);
4170 clang_tokenize(TU, range, &tokens, &num_tokens);
4171
4172 if (checkForErrors(TU) != 0) {
4173 errorCode = -1;
4174 goto teardown;
4175 }
4176
4177 cursors = (CXCursor *)malloc(num_tokens * sizeof(CXCursor));
4178 assert(cursors);
4179 clang_annotateTokens(TU, tokens, num_tokens, cursors);
4180
4181 if (checkForErrors(TU) != 0) {
4182 errorCode = -1;
4183 goto teardown;
4184 }
4185
4186 skipped_ranges = clang_getSkippedRanges(TU, file);
4187 for (i = 0; i != skipped_ranges->count; ++i) {
4188 unsigned start_line, start_column, end_line, end_column;
4189 clang_getSpellingLocation(clang_getRangeStart(skipped_ranges->ranges[i]),
4190 0, &start_line, &start_column, 0);
4191 clang_getSpellingLocation(clang_getRangeEnd(skipped_ranges->ranges[i]),
4192 0, &end_line, &end_column, 0);
4193 printf("Skipping: ");
4194 PrintExtent(stdout, start_line, start_column, end_line, end_column);
4195 printf("\n");
4196 }
4197 clang_disposeSourceRangeList(skipped_ranges);
4198
4199 for (i = 0; i != num_tokens; ++i) {
4200 const char *kind = "<unknown>";
4201 CXString spelling = clang_getTokenSpelling(TU, tokens[i]);
4202 CXSourceRange extent = clang_getTokenExtent(TU, tokens[i]);
4203 unsigned start_line, start_column, end_line, end_column;
4204
4205 switch (clang_getTokenKind(tokens[i])) {
4206 case CXToken_Punctuation: kind = "Punctuation"; break;
4207 case CXToken_Keyword: kind = "Keyword"; break;
4208 case CXToken_Identifier: kind = "Identifier"; break;
4209 case CXToken_Literal: kind = "Literal"; break;
4210 case CXToken_Comment: kind = "Comment"; break;
4211 }
4212 clang_getSpellingLocation(clang_getRangeStart(extent),
4213 0, &start_line, &start_column, 0);
4214 clang_getSpellingLocation(clang_getRangeEnd(extent),
4215 0, &end_line, &end_column, 0);
4216 printf("%s: \"%s\" ", kind, clang_getCString(spelling));
4217 clang_disposeString(spelling);
4218 PrintExtent(stdout, start_line, start_column, end_line, end_column);
4219 if (!clang_isInvalid(cursors[i].kind)) {
4220 printf(" ");
4221 PrintCursor(cursors[i], NULL);
4222 }
4223 printf("\n");
4224 }
4225 free(cursors);
4226 clang_disposeTokens(TU, tokens, num_tokens);
4227
4228 teardown:
4229 PrintDiagnostics(TU);
4230 clang_disposeTranslationUnit(TU);
4231 clang_disposeIndex(CIdx);
4232 free(filename);
4233 free_remapped_files(unsaved_files, num_unsaved_files);
4234 return errorCode;
4235}

4243 CXString wd;

4307 }

4321/******************************************************************************/
4322/* USR printing. */
4323/******************************************************************************/
4324
4325static int insufficient_usr(const char *kind, const char *usage) {
4326 fprintf(stderr, "USR for '%s' requires: %s\n", kind, usage);
4327 return 1;
4328}
4329
4330static unsigned isUSR(const char *s) {
4331 return s[0] == 'c' && s[1] == ':';
4332}
4333
4334static int not_usr(const char *s, const char *arg) {
4335 fprintf(stderr, "'%s' argument ('%s') is not a USR\n", s, arg);
4336 return 1;
4337}
4338
4339static void print_usr(CXString usr) {
4340 const char *s = clang_getCString(usr);
4341 printf("%s\n", s);
4342 clang_disposeString(usr);
4343}
4344
4345static void display_usrs() {
4346 fprintf(stderr, "-print-usrs options:\n"
4347 " ObjCCategory <class name> <category name>\n"
4348 " ObjCClass <class name>\n"
4349 " ObjCIvar <ivar name> <class USR>\n"
4350 " ObjCMethod <selector> [0=class method|1=instance method] "
4351 "<class USR>\n"
4352 " ObjCProperty <property name> <class USR>\n"
4353 " ObjCProtocol <protocol name>\n");
4354}
4355
4356int print_usrs(const char **I, const char **E) {
4357 while (I != E) {
4358 const char *kind = *I;
4359 unsigned len = strlen(kind);
4360 switch (len) {
4361 case 8:
4362 if (memcmp(kind, "ObjCIvar", 8) == 0) {
4363 if (I + 2 >= E)
4364 return insufficient_usr(kind, "<ivar name> <class USR>");
4365 if (!isUSR(I[2]))
4366 return not_usr("<class USR>", I[2]);
4367 else {
4368 CXString x = createCXString(I[2]);
4369 print_usr(clang_constructUSR_ObjCIvar(I[1], x));
4370 }
4371
4372 I += 3;
4373 continue;
4374 }
4375 break;
4376 case 9:
4377 if (memcmp(kind, "ObjCClass", 9) == 0) {
4378 if (I + 1 >= E)
4379 return insufficient_usr(kind, "<class name>");
4380 print_usr(clang_constructUSR_ObjCClass(I[1]));
4381 I += 2;
4382 continue;
4383 }
4384 break;
4385 case 10:
4386 if (memcmp(kind, "ObjCMethod", 10) == 0) {
4387 if (I + 3 >= E)
4388 return insufficient_usr(kind, "<method selector> "
4389 "[0=class method|1=instance method] <class USR>");
4390 if (!isUSR(I[3]))
4391 return not_usr("<class USR>", I[3]);
4392 else {
4393 CXString x = createCXString(I[3]);
4394 print_usr(clang_constructUSR_ObjCMethod(I[1], atoi(I[2]), x));
4395 }
4396 I += 4;
4397 continue;
4398 }
4399 break;
4400 case 12:
4401 if (memcmp(kind, "ObjCCategory", 12) == 0) {
4402 if (I + 2 >= E)
4403 return insufficient_usr(kind, "<class name> <category name>");
4404 print_usr(clang_constructUSR_ObjCCategory(I[1], I[2]));
4405 I += 3;
4406 continue;
4407 }
4408 if (memcmp(kind, "ObjCProtocol", 12) == 0) {
4409 if (I + 1 >= E)
4410 return insufficient_usr(kind, "<protocol name>");
4411 print_usr(clang_constructUSR_ObjCProtocol(I[1]));
4412 I += 2;
4413 continue;
4414 }
4415 if (memcmp(kind, "ObjCProperty", 12) == 0) {
4416 if (I + 2 >= E)
4417 return insufficient_usr(kind, "<property name> <class USR>");
4418 if (!isUSR(I[2]))
4419 return not_usr("<class USR>", I[2]);
4420 else {
4421 CXString x = createCXString(I[2]);
4422 print_usr(clang_constructUSR_ObjCProperty(I[1], x));
4423 }
4424 I += 3;
4425 continue;
4426 }
4427 break;
4428 default:
4429 break;
4430 }
4431 break;
4432 }
4433
4434 if (I != E) {
4435 fprintf(stderr, "Invalid USR kind: %s\n", *I);
4436 display_usrs();
4437 return 1;
4438 }
4439 return 0;
4440}
4441
4442int print_usrs_file(const char *file_name) {
4443 char line[2048];
4444 const char *args[128];
4445 unsigned numChars = 0;
4446
4447 FILE *fp = fopen(file_name, "r");
4448 if (!fp) {
4449 fprintf(stderr, "error: cannot open '%s'\n", file_name);
4450 return 1;
4451 }
4452
4453 /* This code is not really all that safe, but it works fine for testing. */
4454 while (!feof(fp)) {
4455 char c = fgetc(fp);
4456 if (c == '\n') {
4457 unsigned i = 0;
4458 const char *s = 0;
4459
4460 if (numChars == 0)
4461 continue;
4462
4463 line[numChars] = '\0';
4464 numChars = 0;
4465
4466 if (line[0] == '/' && line[1] == '/')
4467 continue;
4468
4469 s = strtok(line, " ");
4470 while (s) {
4471 args[i] = s;
4472 ++i;
4473 s = strtok(0, " ");
4474 }
4475 if (print_usrs(&args[0], &args[i]))
4476 return 1;
4477 }
4478 else
4479 line[numChars++] = c;
4480 }
4481
4482 fclose(fp);
4483 return 0;
4484}

4486/******************************************************************************/
4487/* Command line processing. */
4488/******************************************************************************/
4489int write_pch_file(const char *filename, int argc, const char *argv[]) {
4490 CXIndex Idx;
4491 CXTranslationUnit TU;
4492 struct CXUnsavedFile *unsaved_files = 0;
4493 int num_unsaved_files = 0;
4494 enum CXErrorCode Err;
4495 int result = 0;
4496
4497 Idx = clang_createIndex(/* excludeDeclsFromPCH */1, /* displayDiagnostics=*/1);
4498
4499 if (parse_remapped_files(argc, argv, 0, &unsaved_files, &num_unsaved_files)) {
4500 clang_disposeIndex(Idx);
4501 return -1;
4502 }
4503
4504 Err = clang_parseTranslationUnit2(
4505 Idx, 0, argv + num_unsaved_files, argc - num_unsaved_files,
4506 unsaved_files, num_unsaved_files,
4507 CXTranslationUnit_Incomplete |
4508 CXTranslationUnit_DetailedPreprocessingRecord |
4509 CXTranslationUnit_ForSerialization,
4510 &TU);
4511 if (Err != CXError_Success) {
4512 fprintf(stderr, "Unable to load translation unit!\n");
4513 describeLibclangFailure(Err);
4514 free_remapped_files(unsaved_files, num_unsaved_files);
4515 clang_disposeTranslationUnit(TU);
4516 clang_disposeIndex(Idx);
4517 return 1;
4518 }
4519
4520 switch (clang_saveTranslationUnit(TU, filename,
4521 clang_defaultSaveOptions(TU))) {
4522 case CXSaveError_None:
4523 break;
4524
4525 case CXSaveError_TranslationErrors:
4526 fprintf(stderr, "Unable to write PCH file %s: translation errors\n",
4527 filename);
4528 result = 2;
4529 break;
4530
4531 case CXSaveError_InvalidTU:
4532 fprintf(stderr, "Unable to write PCH file %s: invalid translation unit\n",
4533 filename);
4534 result = 3;
4535 break;
4536
4537 case CXSaveError_Unknown:
4538 default:
4539 fprintf(stderr, "Unable to write PCH file %s: unknown error \n", filename);
4540 result = 1;
4541 break;
4542 }
4543
4544 clang_disposeTranslationUnit(TU);
4545 free_remapped_files(unsaved_files, num_unsaved_files);
4546 clang_disposeIndex(Idx);
4547 return result;
4548}

4598static void printRanges(CXDiagnostic D, unsigned indent) {
4599 unsigned i, n = clang_getDiagnosticNumRanges(D);
4600
4601 for (i = 0; i < n; ++i) {
4602 CXSourceLocation Start, End;
4603 CXSourceRange SR = clang_getDiagnosticRange(D, i);
4604 Start = clang_getRangeStart(SR);
4605 End = clang_getRangeEnd(SR);
4606
4607 printIndent(indent);

4609 printLocation(Start);

4616static void printFixIts(CXDiagnostic D, unsigned indent) {
4617 unsigned i, n = clang_getDiagnosticNumFixIts(D);
4618 fprintf(stderr, "Number FIXITs = %d\n", n);
4619 for (i = 0 ; i < n; ++i) {
4620 CXSourceRange ReplacementRange;
4621 CXString text;
4622 text = clang_getDiagnosticFixIt(D, i, &ReplacementRange);
4623

4626 printLocation(clang_getRangeStart(ReplacementRange));
4627 fprintf(stderr, " - ");
4628 printLocation(clang_getRangeEnd(ReplacementRange));

4634static void printDiagnosticSet(CXDiagnosticSet Diags, unsigned indent) {
4635 unsigned i, n;
4636
4637 if (!Diags)
4638 return;
4639
4640 n = clang_getNumDiagnosticsInSet(Diags);
4641 for (i = 0; i < n; ++i) {
4642 CXSourceLocation DiagLoc;
4643 CXDiagnostic D;
4644 CXFile File;
4645 CXString FileName, DiagSpelling, DiagOption, DiagCat;
4646 unsigned line, column, offset;
4647 const char *DiagOptionStr = 0, *DiagCatStr = 0;
4648
4649 D = clang_getDiagnosticInSet(Diags, i);
4650 DiagLoc = clang_getDiagnosticLocation(D);
4651 clang_getExpansionLocation(DiagLoc, &File, &line, &column, &offset);
4652 FileName = clang_getFileName(File);
4653 DiagSpelling = clang_getDiagnosticSpelling(D);
4654
4655 printIndent(indent);
4656
4657 fprintf(stderr, "%s:%d:%d: %s: %s",
4658 clang_getCString(FileName),
4659 line,
4660 column,
4661 getSeverityString(clang_getDiagnosticSeverity(D)),
4662 clang_getCString(DiagSpelling));
4663
4664 DiagOption = clang_getDiagnosticOption(D, 0);
4665 DiagOptionStr = clang_getCString(DiagOption);
4666 if (DiagOptionStr) {
4667 fprintf(stderr, " [%s]", DiagOptionStr);
4668 }
4669
4670 DiagCat = clang_getDiagnosticCategoryText(D);
4671 DiagCatStr = clang_getCString(DiagCat);
4672 if (DiagCatStr) {
4673 fprintf(stderr, " [%s]", DiagCatStr);
4674 }
4675
4676 fprintf(stderr, "\n");
4677
4678 printRanges(D, indent);
4679 printFixIts(D, indent);
4680
4681 /* Print subdiagnostics. */
4682 printDiagnosticSet(clang_getChildDiagnostics(D), indent+2);
4683
4684 clang_disposeString(FileName);
4685 clang_disposeString(DiagSpelling);
4686 clang_disposeString(DiagOption);
4687 clang_disposeString(DiagCat);
4688 }
4689}

4795int cindextest_main(int argc, const char **argv) {
4796 clang_enableStackTraces();
4797 if (argc > 2 && strcmp(argv[1], "-read-diagnostics") == 0)
4798 return read_diagnostics(argv[2]);
4799 if (argc > 2 && strstr(argv[1], "-code-completion-at=") == argv[1])
4800 return perform_code_completion(argc, argv, 0);
4801 if (argc > 2 && strstr(argv[1], "-code-completion-timing=") == argv[1])
4802 return perform_code_completion(argc, argv, 1);
4803 if (argc > 2 && strstr(argv[1], "-cursor-at=") == argv[1])
4804 return inspect_cursor_at(argc, argv, "-cursor-at=", inspect_print_cursor);
4805 if (argc > 2 && strstr(argv[1], "-evaluate-cursor-at=") == argv[1])
4806 return inspect_cursor_at(argc, argv, "-evaluate-cursor-at=",
4807 inspect_evaluate_cursor);
4808 if (argc > 2 && strstr(argv[1], "-get-macro-info-cursor-at=") == argv[1])
4809 return inspect_cursor_at(argc, argv, "-get-macro-info-cursor-at=",
4810 inspect_macroinfo_cursor);
4811 if (argc > 2 && strstr(argv[1], "-file-refs-at=") == argv[1])
4812 return find_file_refs_at(argc, argv);
4813 if (argc > 2 && strstr(argv[1], "-file-includes-in=") == argv[1])
4814 return find_file_includes_in(argc, argv);
4815 if (argc > 2 && strcmp(argv[1], "-index-file") == 0)
4816 return index_file(argc - 2, argv + 2, /*full=*/0);
4817 if (argc > 2 && strcmp(argv[1], "-index-file-full") == 0)
4818 return index_file(argc - 2, argv + 2, /*full=*/1);
4819 if (argc > 2 && strcmp(argv[1], "-index-tu") == 0)
4820 return index_tu(argc - 2, argv + 2);
4821 if (argc > 2 && strcmp(argv[1], "-index-compile-db") == 0)
4822 return index_compile_db(argc - 2, argv + 2);
4823 else if (argc >= 4 && strncmp(argv[1], "-test-load-tu", 13) == 0) {
4824 CXCursorVisitor I = GetVisitor(argv[1] + 13);
4825 if (I)
4826 return perform_test_load_tu(argv[2], argv[3], argc >= 5 ? argv[4] : 0, I,
4827 NULL);
4828 }
4829 else if (argc >= 5 && strncmp(argv[1], "-test-load-source-reparse", 25) == 0){
4830 CXCursorVisitor I = GetVisitor(argv[1] + 25);
4831 if (I) {
4832 int trials = atoi(argv[2]);
4833 return perform_test_reparse_source(argc - 4, argv + 4, trials, argv[3], I,
4834 NULL);
4835 }
4836 }
4837 else if (argc >= 4 && strncmp(argv[1], "-test-load-source", 17) == 0) {
4838 CXCursorVisitor I = GetVisitor(argv[1] + 17);
4839
4840 PostVisitTU postVisit = 0;
4841 if (strstr(argv[1], "-memory-usage"))
4842 postVisit = PrintMemoryUsage;
4843
4844 if (I)
4845 return perform_test_load_source(argc - 3, argv + 3, argv[2], I,
4846 postVisit);
4847 }
4848 else if (argc >= 3 && strcmp(argv[1], "-single-file-parse") == 0)
4849 return perform_single_file_parse(argv[2]);
4850 else if (argc >= 4 && strcmp(argv[1], "-test-file-scan") == 0)
4851 return perform_file_scan(argv[2], argv[3],
4852 argc >= 5 ? argv[4] : 0);
4853 else if (argc > 2 && strstr(argv[1], "-test-annotate-tokens=") == argv[1])
4854 return perform_token_annotation(argc, argv);
4855 else if (argc > 2 && strcmp(argv[1], "-test-inclusion-stack-source") == 0)
4856 return perform_test_load_source(argc - 2, argv + 2, "all", NULL,
4857 PrintInclusionStack);
4858 else if (argc > 2 && strcmp(argv[1], "-test-inclusion-stack-tu") == 0)
4859 return perform_test_load_tu(argv[2], "all", NULL, NULL,
4860 PrintInclusionStack);
4861 else if (argc > 2 && strcmp(argv[1], "-test-print-linkage-source") == 0)
4862 return perform_test_load_source(argc - 2, argv + 2, "all", PrintLinkage,
4863 NULL);
4864 else if (argc > 2 && strcmp(argv[1], "-test-print-visibility") == 0)
4865 return perform_test_load_source(argc - 2, argv + 2, "all", PrintVisibility,
4866 NULL);
4867 else if (argc > 2 && strcmp(argv[1], "-test-print-type") == 0)
4868 return perform_test_load_source(argc - 2, argv + 2, "all",
4869 PrintType, 0);
4870 else if (argc > 2 && strcmp(argv[1], "-test-print-type-size") == 0)
4871 return perform_test_load_source(argc - 2, argv + 2, "all",
4872 PrintTypeSize, 0);
4873 else if (argc > 2 && strcmp(argv[1], "-test-print-type-declaration") == 0)
4874 return perform_test_load_source(argc - 2, argv + 2, "all",
4875 PrintTypeDeclaration, 0);
4876 else if (argc > 2 && strcmp(argv[1], "-test-print-decl-attributes") == 0)
4877 return perform_test_load_source(argc - 2, argv + 2, "all",
4878 PrintDeclAttributes, 0);
4879 else if (argc > 2 && strcmp(argv[1], "-test-print-bitwidth") == 0)
4880 return perform_test_load_source(argc - 2, argv + 2, "all",
4881 PrintBitWidth, 0);
4882 else if (argc > 2 && strcmp(argv[1], "-test-print-mangle") == 0)
4883 return perform_test_load_tu(argv[2], "all", NULL, PrintMangledName, NULL);
4884 else if (argc > 2 && strcmp(argv[1], "-test-print-manglings") == 0)
4885 return perform_test_load_tu(argv[2], "all", NULL, PrintManglings, NULL);
4886 else if (argc > 2 && strcmp(argv[1], "-test-print-target-info") == 0)
4887 return print_target_info(argc - 2, argv + 2);
4888 else if (argc > 1 && strcmp(argv[1], "-print-usr") == 0) {
4889 if (argc > 2)
4890 return print_usrs(argv + 2, argv + argc);
4891 else {
4892 display_usrs();
4893 return 1;
4894 }
4895 }
4896 else if (argc > 2 && strcmp(argv[1], "-print-usr-file") == 0)
4897 return print_usrs_file(argv[2]);
4898 else if (argc > 2 && strcmp(argv[1], "-write-pch") == 0)
4899 return write_pch_file(argv[2], argc - 3, argv + 3);
4900 else if (argc > 2 && strcmp(argv[1], "-compilation-db") == 0)
4901 return perform_test_compilation_db(argv[argc-1], argc - 3, argv + 2);
4902 else if (argc == 2 && strcmp(argv[1], "-print-build-session-timestamp") == 0)
4903 return perform_print_build_session_timestamp();
4904
4905 print_usage();
4906 return 1;
4907}

4911/* We intentionally run in a separate thread to ensure we at least minimal
4912 * testing of a multithreaded environment (for example, having a reduced stack
4913 * size). */
4914
4915typedef struct thread_info {
4916 int (*main_func)(int argc, const char **argv);
4917 int argc;
4918 const char **argv;
4919 int result;
4920} thread_info;
4921void thread_runner(void *client_data_v) {
4922 thread_info *client_data = client_data_v;
4923 client_data->result = client_data->main_func(client_data->argc,
4924 client_data->argv);
4925}
4926
4927static void flush_atexit(void) {
4928 /* stdout, and surprisingly even stderr, are not always flushed on process
4929 * and thread exit, particularly when the system is under heavy load. */
4930 fflush(stdout);
4931 fflush(stderr);
4932}
4933
4934int main(int argc, const char **argv) {
4935 thread_info client_data;
4936
4937 atexit(flush_atexit);
4938
4939#ifdef CLANG_HAVE_LIBXML
4940 LIBXML_TEST_VERSION
4941#endif
4942
4943 if (argc > 1 && strcmp(argv[1], "core") == 0)
4944 return indextest_core_main(argc, argv);
4945
4946 client_data.main_func = cindextest_main;
4947 client_data.argc = argc;
4948 client_data.argv = argv;
4949
4950 if (getenv("CINDEXTEST_NOTHREADS"))
4951 return client_data.main_func(client_data.argc, client_data.argv);
4952
4953 clang_executeOnThread(thread_runner, &client_data, 0);
4954 return client_data.result;
4955}
